<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Government Work Report Down-to-Earth and Inspiring: NPC Deputies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Deputies to the National People's
Congress in session here praised the government work report
delivered by Premier Li Peng at this morning's session as
"down-to-earth and inspiring" in group discussions this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Xu Kuangdi, mayor of Shanghai, said the past five years
are a period when Shanghai as well as China as a whole have had
the fastest economic growth and social development. It has been
achieved under the guidance of Deng Xiaoping Theory, he said.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Abudul'ahat Abdurixit, chairman of the Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region, commented that besides being a summary of the
past five years, the report explains China's current economic
situation and sets forth concrete measures to tackle problems.
</P>
<P>
"It conforms with realities of the country and objective laws
of economic development," he said.
</P>
<P>
Chen Wanzhi, a deputy from Chongqing University, said the
report does not dodge problems and contradictions. "Goals and
measures put forward in the report are realistic," he said.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the financial reform part of the report, Deputy
Ni Guangzu, a banker from Yunnan province, said China has made
great strides in reform of its financial system.
</P>
<P>
"Facts have proved that the principles, policies and measures
adopted by the central government in the financial field are
correct," he said.
</P>
<P>
The report has emphasized the importance of stability, said
Deputy Liu Mingzu, secretary of the Mongolian Regional Committee
of the Communist Party of China. The 50-year history of Inner
Mongolia Autonomous Region has proved that it is of great
significance to safeguard national unity and social stability, he
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
