<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Bars Agriculture, Films From Trade Pact With U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The European Union's (EU) planned
negotiations with the United States would not cover the touchy
sectors of agriculture and audio-video services.
</P>
<P>
The United States must understand the EU's point in this regard
before the negotiations start, the European Commission, the EU's
executive body, said in a press release on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"It's only under these conditions that negotiations (with the
United State) have any chance at all of reaching a satisfactory
conclusion," an EU spokesman was quoted as saying in the release.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman was reporting on Commission President Jacques
Santer's decision after the EU executive body discussed, for the
first time, plans to create closer trade ties with the United
States.
</P>
<P>
The EU and the United States have long been at odds over the
issues of agriculture and audio-video services.
</P>
<P>
The Uruguay Round of talks on global trade liberalization was
almost killed as the United States tried to scale down the
European system of subsidies to farmers and French demands for
protection of its audio-video industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
