<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 300 Killed in Flash Floods in Southwestern Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The death toll in the worst
floods in southwestern Pakistan has risen to 300 with 1,500 people
still missing on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
More than 3,700 houses have been completely destroyed while
8,000 partially damaged in the remote Makran Division of the
Balochistan Province, which was hit by devastating floods on
Tuesday following 36-hours of torrential rains, according to
reports reaching here Thursday evening.
</P>
<P>
The gushing flood waters also took with them 7,200 head of
cattle while nearly 198 villages have been affected by the floods.
Turbat, division headquarters of Makran, is still cut off from the
rest of the country.
</P>
<P>
Relief and rescue operations, jointly launched by the army,
navy and civilians, in the flood-affected areas of Makran are
continuing in full swing.
</P>
<P>
A vast area along the flooded River Dasht has been devastated
and it is feared that the death toll may rise to more than 1,000,
relief officials said.
</P>
<P>
It was also feared that if precautionary measures were not
taken by the people and the concerned officials, an epidemic could
break out in the flood-affected areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
