<HEADLINE> France Concerned About Report on Police Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 5 (Xinhua) -- France Thursday expressed concern
over reports from Yugoslavia that the Yugoslav security forces
have launched an operation against a village of ethnic Albanians
in the province of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
"If these reports are confirmed, they would attest an
escalation of the violence which went in the opposite direction of
the appeal for restraint by the international community and
France," said French Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Anne
Gazeau-Secret.
</P>
<P>
She said that France condemns violence exerted by any side of
the conflict and "firmly reminds the authorities of the Federal
Republic of Yugoslavia that only dialogue will allow to find a
political solution to the question of Kosovo."
</P>
<P>
The Interior Ministry of Serbia confirmed that security forces
conducted an operation in the region of Srbica Thursday morning
after two Serb policemen were wounded in an ambush by Albanian
"terrorists." 
</P>
