<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Enzhu on the Good Beginning of the Hong Kong SAR (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Director of Xinhua News Agency
Hong Kong Branch Jiang Enzhu today said the policy of "one
country, two systems" has been successfully implemented in the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) since it return to
the motherland eight months ago.
</P>
<P>
When deliberating Premier Li Peng's government work report
together with other deputies from the Hong Kong SAR, Jiang said
the Hong Kong SAR is politically stable after its eight-month
operation under the Basic Law, and all facets of social life
is normal.
</P>
<P>
"In his report Premier Li particularly elaborated on the great
historical significance of the Hong Kong's return and the present
situation of the SAR, and reaffirmed the central government's
support to the SAR government. Li especially pointed out that the
SAR has had a good beginning and Hong Kong's future will be even
brighter. This conclusion absolutely tallies with facts," he said.
</P>
<P>
Since Hong Kong's return eight months ago, its social system
and the way of life have remained unchanged and laws have been
kept basically intact, he said. The SAR government has
independently carried out effective administration of Hong Kong
society in accordance with the Basic Law, and its residents fully
enjoy the rights and freedom as provided by the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong continues to maintain its status as an international
financial, trade and shipping center as well as the status of free
port," he acknowledged.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that despite attack by the Asian financial
crisis since last October, Hong Kong still achieved a steady
economic growth. The measures taken by the SAR government have
been successful in pegging the Hong Kong dollar to the US dollar,
and maintaining the economic and financial stability on the whole.
</P>
<P>
"The Hong Kong SAR now enjoys social stability, and its
residents have a sense of security and confide in the SAR
government," he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that since its return to the motherland, Hong
Kong has maintained and further reinforced its relations with the
international community.
</P>
<P>
"All these facts demonstrate that the policy of `one country
two systems' has been turned into reality, and is increasingly
showing its great vitality," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
