<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0011 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Enzhu on the Good Beginning of the Hong Kong SAR (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He attributed the factors underlining the achievements of the
Hong Kong SAR to the unswerving efforts made by the central
government to implement the policies of "one country, two systems"
and "Hong Kong people administering Hong Kong" with a high degree
of autonomy, and local residents' support to these policies; the
efficient leadership of the SAR government; as well as the
effective economic operating mechanism and financial management
principles.
</P>
<P>
"The most critical factor is the powerful backing of the
motherland," he acknowledged, adding that many noted personalities
in Hong Kong held that the country's good economic and social
situation has been playing a positive role in stabilizing Hong
Kong economy during the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Looking ahead, he added, the policy of "one country, two
systems" and the Basic Law will be implemented in an all-round
way, Hong Kong's prosperity and stability will continue to be
maintained, and cooperation in all economic and social sectors
between the SAR and the interior area will be further promoted
and expanded.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong will surely have an even brighter future," Jiang
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
