<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Albania Calls for European, U.S. Diplomatic Action </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Albanian Foreign Minister Pascal
Milo Thursday called on European Union and the United States to
stage a diplomatic intervention in the Yugoslav province of Kosovo
to prevent an escalation of violence there.
</P>
<P>
"I believe in a united European-American diplomatic action to
resolve the crisis in Kosovo," Milo told Agence France-Presse
after he arrived in the French capital to discuss with his French
counterpart Hubert Vedrine the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
Milo said that the international community, which has all the
means for an intervention, should urgently intervene before it is
too late and turns into another Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
"In the case of a new conflict in the Balkans, Albanians will
not be the only one to pay the price, but also the Europeans, and
for a longtime," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that for the time being, the crisis in Kosovo has not
"attained such a dimension as they would spill beyond the borders
of Kosovo" into Albania and Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
France has urged both sides of the conflict in Kosovo to remain
calm and seek a solution through dialogue.
</P>
<P>
France has also asked the Serbian government to restore the
statute of autonomy for Kosovo, which was suppressed in 1989.
</P>
</TEXT>
