<HEADLINE> World Bank Launches US Dollar Bond Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank announced here
Thursday that it would launch U.S. dollar global bond issue soon.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank has mandated Goldman Sachs, J.P. Morgan and SBC
Warburg Dillon Read of Switzerland to jointly lead-manage a USD
global bond transaction, which is expected to be launched in the
coming days.
</P>
<P>
The issue is expected to have a 5-year maturity and the size of
the transaction will range from 3 billion dollars up to 5 billion
dollars.
</P>
<P>
It would be the World Bank's 14th USD global bond since the
first global bond was issued in 1989. 
</P>
</TEXT>
