<HEADLINE> UK Interest Rate Remains Unchanged at 7.25 pct </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Britain's central bank the Bank of
England decided on Thursday not to raise interest rates this
month, leaving the base rate unchanged at 7.25 percent.
</P>
<P>
The bank announced the decision at midday after its monetary
policy committee had held its monthly meeting which began on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the bank faced a difficult decision in
view of the evidence of a deepening split in the economy.
</P>
<P>
Manufacturing growth has almost come to a standstill whilst the
service sector continues to boom, running at its highest level for
seven months.
</P>
<P>
The decision is said to have pleased the City, where share
prices have been plunging over the last two days, partly on the
back of fears of a rise.
</P>
<P>
UK interest rates last rose in November, the fifth hike since
last year's general election. 
</P>
</TEXT>
