<HEADLINE> UN Sets New Deadline for Angolan Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations has set
a new deadline of March 15 for the completion of the remaining
tasks in the peace process in Angola, UN spokesman's office
announced on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"The United Nations Secretary-General's Deputy Special
Representative for Angola Behrooz Sadry represented the Angolan
parties on Tuesday with a proposal for the new deadline of March
15 for the completion of remaining tasks in the undergoing peace
process," a UN spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the parties were now discussing the
proposals.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Security Council has continued expressing
its concern at the general situation in Angola which remains
precarious. The peace process has stalled since a new timetable on
the implementation of the remaining tasks in the peace process was
adopted in January. The delay has been caused mainly by the
National Union for the total independence of Angola(UNITA).
</P>
