<HEADLINE> IDB Backs Health Service Modernization in El Salvador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) announced here Thursday the approval of a 20.7 million
U.S. dollar loan to El Salvador in support of the modernization of
its health system.
</P>
<P>
The program, which also includes two pilot projects, is aimed
to improve the efficiency, effectiveness and equity of health
services for the most disadvantaged population in the two pilot
areas of Santa Ana and San Miguel.
</P>
<P>
In addition, two public hospitals will be transformed into
model facilities that are governed technical assistance, training
and some equipment for the hospitals.
</P>
<P>
At the national level, the project will assist the
reorganization and decentralization of key ministerial functions,
including health programs and the financial management system.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the program is some 26.1 million dollars.
Apart from the IDB loan, local counterpart will fund total 5.4
million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
