<HEADLINE> UK Mobile Phone Cost is Highest in World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Customers of mobile phone in
Britain are paying some of the highest charges in the world and
the country's telecommunications watchdog Oftel is to order cuts
in the cost of mobile phone calls, according to a BBC television
report Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The regulator is to refer the matter to the Monopolies and
Mergers Commission, and Director-General Don Cruickshand will
demand that the cost of mobile phone calls from fixed lines run by
companies like British Telecommunications (BT) be cut from 32
pence (0.53 US dollar) per minute to 20 pence (0.33 US dollar).
</P>
<P>
He said BT and the two biggest mobile networks, Vodafone and
Cellnet, were particularly guilty of overchanging.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the cost of making a call with a U.K.
operator can be up to 70 percent higher than elsewhere in Europe,
while monthly rental fees can be eight times higher. 
</P>
</TEXT>
