February 23 defused the crisis over the arms inspections in Iraq
and avoided a possible U.S. military strike against Iraqi targets.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has to give the U.N. arms inspectors an unfettered and
unconditional access to eight presidential palaces suspected of
hiding weapons of mass destruction and weapons programs.
</P>
<P>
GCC groups Saudi Arabia, Kuwait, the United Arab Emirates,
Oman, Bahrain and Qatar.
</P>
<P>
Hujailan also urged in his statement all parties concerned to
exert all efforts to push forward the Middle East peace process.
