send delegates since it might not be possible for all its 15
members to attend the event.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with Annan, Ikimi said the capacity of the
ECOWAS peace-keeping force ECOMOG needed to be enhanced to
effectively carry out its mandate in Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
ECOMOG ousted the military junta in the Sierra Leone capital
Freetown about three weeks ago and has since been carrying out
disarmament of combatants in the war-torn country.
</P>
<P>
Ikimi urged the U.N. to deploy a military observer mission to
Sierra Leone to join ECOMOG in the task of disarmament and boost
the security in the country.
</P>
<P>
He also called for an increase in humanitarian assistance to
that country to alleviate its people's suffering. 
