developments relevant to the role of the United Nations with
regard to Iraq," the UN chief said.
</P>
<P>
"He will lend his support to existing United Nations activities
in the arms control, humanitarian and economic and social fields
while giving special attention to any crisis or problem which
might benefit from intervention by United Nations Headquarters,"
the Secretary-General said.  
