<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kohl's Coalition Battered in Parliamentary Vote on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 5 (Xinhua) -- German Chancellor Helmut Kohl's
ruling coalition suffered a major setback today as some
parliamentary members from his own camp joined the opposition
parties in pushing through a legislation limiting police's power
to use bugging against organized crimes.
</P>
<P>
The amendment drafted by the opposition Social Democratic Party
(SPD) to immunize doctors, lawyers and journalists from police
bugging was adopted by a vote of 329 to 322 in the lower house of
the German parliament on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
About ten rebels from the Free Democratic Party (FDP), the
junior partner of Kohl's ruling coalition, had voted in favor of
the draft.
</P>
<P>
The voting result was cheered by the opposition parties as
another defeat for Kohl within one week after his Christian
Democratic Union (CDU) was trounced by the SPD in the regional
elections at the western German Lower Saxony state last Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The state elections has sealed the nomination of Gerhard
Schroeder as the SPD challenger to Kohl in the September general
elections, an option which is likely to pose the most serious
threat to Kohl's bid to seek an unprecedented fifth term as German
chancellor.
</P>
<P>
"Kohl's coalition has fallen apart," said a SPD parliamentary
leader, Peter Struck. Joschka Fischer, leader of the opposition
Greens party, also interpreted the bugging vote as "a continuation
of the farewell phase" of Kohl's ruling coalition consisting of
CDU, its Bavarian sister party Christian Social Union (CSU) and
FDP.
</P>
<P>
While expressing disappointment at today's voting result, the
CDU however dismissed the notion that the ruling coalition is in a
crisis.
</P>
<P>
The former FDP justice minister of Germany, Sabine
Leutheusser-Schnarrenberger, also made a talk to play down her
party's defection today, saying that it was quite natural for some
FDP members to have different opinions on such an important
constitutional issue as the bugging practice. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
