<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0071 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Conglomerates Record Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The 70 largest conglomerates in
south China's Guangdong Province reported combined profits of
12.96 billion yuan (1.56 billion US dollars) in 1997, a
year-on-year rise of 11.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The increase, which resulted from efforts to reduce or
eliminate the production of both unmarketable product and items
with low demand, reversed the downturn in efficiency recorded in
early 1997.
</P>
<P>
In addition, various groups introduced organizational
restructuring to establish integrated production, scientific
research and marketing.
</P>
<P>
Fifty-five industrial enterprise groups accounted for 10.98
billion yuan of the aforementioned total profits, with 15 groups
in the commercial, trade and construction sectors accounting for
the balance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
