<HEADLINE> Restructuring plan draws Public Response (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tian Chengping, secretary of the Qinghai CPC Provincial Party
Committee, said, "The enthusiastic applause from NPC deputies
showed that the government plan on institutional restructuring has
already been approved."
</P>
<P>
Wang Hanmin, vice governor of northwest China's Qinghai
Province, said that the existing government structure was set up
in the course of a planned economy. It is now disadvantageous to
China's economic growth, reforms and a shift of economic
structuring and economic growth mode.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Dongsheng, a deputy from northeast China's Liaoning
Province, said the current institutional restructuring is a though
reform which involves a wide range of fields.
</P>
<P>
Lu Gongxun, chairman of the Standing Committee of the Shanxi
Provincial People's Congress, described the institutional
restructuring as an issue of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Jilin Governor Wang Yunkun said that in the course of market
economy, government institutions must be simplified, unified and
highly effective. This is an effective measure to overcome
bureaucracy.
</P>
<P>
Lu Kejian, chairman of the Ninth Provincial People's Congress
in Gansu, said, "State Councillor Luo Gan promised that the
government institutional restructuring would be implemented soon
after it is approved. Such speedy work style has an epoch-making
significance.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan deputy Zhang Yingwen said that institutional
restructuring is a big issue since the existing government
structure is separated from the practice of market economy, and
hinders the growth of productive forces. So the institutional
restructuring is now feasible and inevitable, he said.  
</P>
