<HEADLINE> CPPCC Members Speak Highly of Government Work Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Many authoritative sources with
the theoretical circles today spoke highly of the eperience
China obtained over the past five years, which was summed up by
Premier Li Peng in his government work report.
</P>
<P>
The theorists, who are attending the First Session of the Ninth
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), heard the premier's report Thursday at the
opening meeting of the First Session of the Ninth National
People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC members reached consensus that the five-point
experience included in the report is of great significance to the
future work of the Chinese government, and should be taken
as the principles for guidance.
</P>
<P>
Gong Yuzhi, deputy director of the Party History Research
Center of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee,
said the experience scored embodies the essence of Deng Xiaoping
Theory and should be observed both at present and in the future.
</P>
<P>
China has shunned major economic fluctuations and maintained
rapid, sound and sustained economic growth, which shows that the
central collective leadership with Jiang Zemin at the core has
become more matured and experienced in controlling complex
situation in the reform and opening-up, Gong said.
</P>
<P>
Yang Chungui, vice-president of the Party School of the CPC
Central Committee, said the valuable experience, which was
obtained in the practice of building socialism, reflects the
country's current specific conditions in a "dialectical and
all-round way."
</P>
<P>
Many theorists said that they are satisfied with the strategies
of revitalizing the country with the use of science and education
and sustainable development, which were eluciated in Li Peng's
report.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Bai Gang, deputy director of the Political Science
Research Institute under the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences,
noted that "the experience will be of great importance to guiding
the country's development into the 21st century."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
