<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0080 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepal Takes Measures to Implement Agriculture Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The Nepali government has taken
a number of measures for the effective implementation of the
country's 20-year Agriculture Perspective Plan, the official RSS
news agency said Friday.
</P>
<P>
These measures include increasing the use of chemical
fertilizers, and small and underground irrigation facilities,
building roads, strengthening agricultural services, making the
agricultural loan system more extensive and boosting the
production of higher-value agricultural products like vegetables,
fruit, dairy products and meat, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
It added that developing agriculture on a commercial basis is
also encouraged in areas where agricultural infrastructure like
roads and irrigation facilities are intact.
</P>
<P>
A one-day workshop was organized here Friday to review progress
made in the past six months in carrying out the agricultural plan
and formulate a strategy for the future.
</P>
<P>
The workshop was jointly organized by Nepal's National Planning
Commission and the Asian Development Bank.
</P>
<P>
The plan, introduced last year, aims to increase agriculture's
growth rate from the present 3 percent to 5 percent and reduce the
population in poverty from 45 percent to 14 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
