<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0082 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party Theorist on Experience of Past Five Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The most important experience for
China in the past five years is adherence to the ideological line
of emancipating the mind and seeking truth from facts, a noted
Party theorist said here today.
</P>
<P>
In an exclusive interview, Xing Bensi, a deputy to the Ninth
National People's Congress, told Xinhua that every success China
has made in the past five years can be attributed to this
ideological line set forth by the late Chinese leader Deng
Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
"We must continue adhering to this line, and further develop it
by combining Deng Xiaoping Theory with new practices," said Xing,
who is a vice president of the Party School of the Communist Party
of China's Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
He said a major reason for China to be able to maintain high
economic growth while keeping inflation at a fairly low level in
recent years is that the government has successfully handled the
relationship between reform, development and stability.
</P>
<P>
"Economic growth, if not accompanied by social stability, can't
bring great benefits to a country and its people," he asserted.
</P>
<P>
He said that although economic development is currently the
central task for China, it's also necessary to seek synchronous
progress in other aspects, such as legal system building, culture,
science and technology and education, for a comprehensive social
advancement.
</P>
<P>
He also praised the central government for having improved its
macro-control capabilities in recent years while developing a
market economic system.
</P>
<P>
"The current major concern of the Chinese society is reform of
state-owned enterprises, which is also an issue of government
macro-control. It's very arduous work, but we have confidence in
doing it well," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He went on to stress the importance of science, technology and
education to China's future development.
</P>
<P>
"The development of science, technology and education will not
only add impetus to China's development in the next few years, but
also enhance the country's competitive edge in the global
community in the next century," he commented.
</P>
<P>
"Deng Xiaoping Theory is the basic guarantee for an all-round
advancement of the cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics into the 21st century," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
