<HEADLINE> Quake-Affected County Schools Open on Schedule </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Some 397 primary and middle
schools in Zhangbei County, an area devastated by a severe
earthquake on January 10, have opened for Spring term on schedule
</P>
<P>
The quake, measuring 6.2 on the Richter scale, hit the area
leaving 47 dead and more than 1,000 seriously injured.
</P>
<P>
Local governments responded by focusing on rebuilding local
schools to accommodate 27,000 primary and middle students.
</P>
<P>
Houses and tents are being used as temporary facilities due to
the massive effort involved in rebuilding schools destroyed
in the quake.
</P>
<P>
The problem has been compounded due to the fact that the region
is located on Loess Plateau which is subject to frequent extended
periods of sub-zero temperatures. 
</P>
