<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yellow River Dam Project Proceeds Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Work on the Yellow River
Xiaolangdi Hydropower Project has proceeded smoothly since the
river was dammed on October 28 last year.
</P>
<P>
The project, located in Luoyang, central China's Henan
Province, is expected to enhance safely during the forthcoming
flood season, according to a local administrative official.
</P>
<P>
The massive project, including the dam which is 1,667 meters
long and 154 meters high, is being constructed at a cost of
34.75 billion yuan, including World Bank loans totalling 1.1
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Approximately 41 percent of the total investment has been
expended to date, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
Flood control facilities, including a cofferdam standing 185
meters in height and a leak-proof water retention wall with a
thickness of 1.2 meters, are scheduled to be completed in time to
control anticipated summer flooding.
</P>
<P>
Three international consortia are carrying out project
contracts, and the first generator is expected to go online in
1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
