<HEADLINE> Hainan Set to Adopt Unleaded Gas Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Hainan, China's southernmost island
province, will adopt an "unleaded gas" policy on April 1 this year
as part of an effort to protect the local environment.
</P>
<P>
Hainan will become the nation's first province to ban the
sale and use of leaded gasoline, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
Hainan currently has well over 110,000 motor vehicles and over
300 gas stations. 
</P>
