<HEADLINE> Russian Swimmers to Race in Icy Siberian River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Some 60 Russian swimmers will race
in the icy waters of a Siberian river in a two-day relay that
began Friday, according to the ITAR-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
Participants in the swimming race on the Charysh river in
Russia's Altai region plan to test new techniques to fight
hypothermia, and hope to earn a mention in the Guinness Book of
Records, said Vladimir Grebenkin, president of the International
Winter Swimming Marathon Association and chief arbiter in the
competition.
</P>
<P>
Swimming in icy ponds and rivers is a tradition in Russia, but
the swimming race in Altai would be the first of its kind,
Grebenkin said. 
</P>
