<HEADLINE> Taiwan Investors Establish 233 Farms in Hainan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Investors from Taiwan have invested
a total capital of close to 200 million US dollars to establish 233
agricultural companies in Hainan, China's southernmost island
province.
</P>
<P>
Local observers attribute the massive influx of funds to local
governments to encourage investments from Taiwan, China's largest
island province.
</P>
<P>
Hainan and Taiwan, two sub-tropical provinces, share similar
natural and geographical conditions, as well as equivalent
experiences in agricultural development.
</P>
<P>
Hainan offers abundant land and labor resources, while Taiwan
features ample technology and financial resources. Observers note
that the combined resources will be highly beneficial for the
future development of agricultural sectors of the two provinces.
 
</P>
