<HEADLINE> Premier on Agriculture, Reform of State-owned Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng today stressed the
importance of agriculture, the reform of state-owned enterprises
and the wellbeing of laid-off workers during a panel discussion of
the First Session of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
"Agriculture should be given priority in economic work,"
because a large proportion of the population in north China's
Hebei Province is engaged in agriculture, Li Peng told the NPC
deputies from province.
</P>
<P>
To achieve sustained and steady growth of agriculture, the
capability to withstand natural calamities should be strengthened,
the structure of agriculture and the mix of farm produce should be
readjusted, and farming production should be industrialized, Li
said.
</P>
<P>
With regard to the reform of the state-owned enterprises, Li
said leading bodies of the enterprises should give guidance to all
workers and staffers, so as to help them become market economy
oriented; and the enterprises should conduct technological
upgrading, and a sound leadership is a decisive factor to
contribute to the good performance of enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Premier Li Peng called on local governments to take
effective measures to the aid of the laid-offs and expand channels
for reemploy them through the means of vocational training and
relocation, so as to ensure smooth reform and social stability.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
