<HEADLINE> Beijing Selects Model High-Tech Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Beijing, the Chinese capital, has
designated 12 model foreign-funded new and high technology
enterprises as part of an effort to guide foreign investments into
related areas.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Mayor Zhang Mao presented the qualification certificates
to the businesses this afternoon. The list includes
Mitsubishi-Stone Semiconductor Co. Ltd, Beijing Murata Electronics
Co. Ltd, Beijing Rhone-Poulenc Eastern Chemicals, Beijing Bell
Telecommunications Equipment Manufacturing Co. Ltd, and Shougang
Motoman Robot Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises, mostly multinational corporations, are
involved in the electronic information, bioengineering,
pharmaceuticals and new materials sectors.
</P>
<P>
Beijing adopted policies to encourage foreign investment in
technology-intensive sectors in May of last year. The
aforementioned firms are expected to serve as models in this
regard and will be granted priority in terms of approvals,
registration, loans, customs formalities and tax reductions.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that the city will add to the list in the future in
an attempt to promote the sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
