<HEADLINE> EximBank Inks Loan Agreement with Cameroon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The agreement calls for EximBank to grant loans totalling 4.2
million US dollars to the corporation, with the latter relending
the funds to a Cameroonian tire plant and tractor assembly plant.
</P>
<P>
The two Cameroonian projects, which China's Gansu Tire Plant
and Wuhan Tractor Plant will establish in cooperation with local
firms, are expected to benefit the growth of Cameroon's rubber,
farm machinery and agricultural sectors, in addition to boosting
China's exports of machinery, equipment and technology.
</P>
<P>
EximBank, a policy-oriented bank established in 1994 to finance
China's exports of electronics, machinery and complete sets of
equipment, was assigned responsibility for granting preferential
Chinese government loans to foreign countries in 1995. By the end
of February this year, EximBank had signed some 30-odd loan
agreements with over a dozen recipient countries, including Sudan,
Cote Divoire, Gabon, Papua New Guinea and Guyana. 
</P>
</TEXT>
