<HEADLINE> Shanghai Bourse Records Slight Fluctuations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Stock Exchange (SSE)
Composite Index closed at 1206.45 points today on the last trading
day of the week, down a mere 0.01 percent when compared to the
previous week.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai bourse witnessed slight fluctuations during the
week as a result of the special Ministry of Finance bond issue of
270 billion yuan to assist state-owned commercial banks.
</P>
<P>
The SSE Composite Index dropped by 18 points to close at
1188.31 points on Monday, but recovered in the following two days
and peaked at 1213.25 points on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Some 167 of 430 shares listed on the SSE recorded rises during
the week, with 252 dropping. Trading in B shares shrank by 6.62
percent while trading of funds and bonds went down 56 percent and
27.1 percent respectively when compared to the previous
week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
