<HEADLINE> British Airway Plane Makes Emergency Landing in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 6 (Xinhua) -- An British airway plane
executed a safe emergency landing at the Ben Gurion Airport in
Tel Aviv Friday, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The plane was forced to make the landing as it suffered from
engine troubles. One of its engines stopped working when a small
explosion occurred in the engine.
</P>
<P>
The Boeing 767 plane, which was departing for London, was
carrying some 250 passengers, but no casualties were reported in
the accident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
