<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0116 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Detailed Plan on Restructuring of State Council (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Luo Gan, state councillor and
secretary-general of the State Council, made detailed explanations
about the blueprint concerning Institutional Restructuring of the
State Council.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the ongoing First Session of the Ninth National
People's Congress (NPC), Luo Gan expounded the restructuring of
departments engaged in macro-economic control and special economic
sectors, those in charge of education, science and technology,
social security and resources, and administrative departments.
</P>
<P>
The main duties of macro-economic departments are to maintain
an overall economic balance, curbing inflation, and optimizing
economic structure so as to achieve a sustained, rapid and sound
development of the economy, Luo Gan said.
</P>
<P>
The State Planning Commission will be renamed the State
Development Planning Commission. The State Economic and Trade
Commission, the Ministry of Finance and the People's Bank of China
will be retained.
</P>
<P>
In an effort to strengthen the State Council's leadership over
economic restructuring, the State Commission for Restructuring the
Economy will be turned into a high-level deliberation body headed
by the premier with relevant ministers serving as its members.
And it will not be included into the series of component
departments under the State Council.
</P>
<P>
The main responsibilities of specialized economic management
departments are to formulate sectoral programs and policies,
readjust the product mix of the sectors, and maintain the order of
competitiveness on equal footing.
</P>
<P>
Such special economic departments should all practice the
separation of administration from business operation, effectively
change their functions and they no longer directly administer
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The relations between government and state-owned enterprises
are as follows: the government will enjoy the owner's equity
according to the amount of capital it has invested into
enterprises, send supervisory commissioners to enterprises who
will oversee the latter's capital operation and profiteering or
money-losing situation.
</P>
<P>
The government will also be held responsible for appraisal,
appointment and removal of principal leaders of enterprises.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0117 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Detailed Plan on Restructuring of State Council (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On the other hand, enterprises will, according to law, manage
the operation on their own, take responsibility for their own
profits and losses, and turn in taxes according to relevant
regulations.
</P>
<P>
In addition, enterprises will be responsible for keeping and
increasing the value of state-owned assets and cannot harm the
rights and interests of owners.
</P>
<P>
The ministries of railways, communications, construction,
agriculture, water resources, foreign trade and economic
cooperation will be kept.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Information Industry will be set up on the
basis of the existing Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications and
Ministry of Electronics Industry.
</P>
<P>
The new ministry will be held responsible for invigorating the
manufacture business of information products, telecommunications
and software industries, formulating sectoral programs, policies
and laws codes, mapping out overall plan for telecommunications
trunk networks (including local and long-distance
telecommunications networks), broadcast and television networks
(including radio and cable television networks), and special-use
telecommunications networks for military departments and other
departments.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, it will exercise sectoral management, allocation of
resources rationally, avoid overlapping projects and ensure
information security,
</P>
<P>
The government functions for information and network
management in the Ministry of Broadcast, Film and Television,
China Aerospace Industry Corporation and the China Aviation
Industry Corporation will be incorporated into the Ministry of
Information Industry.
</P>
<P>
The new ministry will also take charge of the State Postal
Bureau which is to be founded.
</P>
<P>
The Commission of Science, Technology and Industry for National
Defense will be reorganized, assimilating the administrative
functions of the National Defense Department under the State
Planning Commission and various other military industrial
corporations.
</P>
<P>
Various military industrial corporations will be turned into a
number of enterprise groups.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0118 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Detailed Plan on Restructuring of State Council (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The State Aerospace Bureau and the State Atomic Energy Agency
will also be retained, representing the country in foreign
exchanges and, internally, acting as an institution of the
Commission of Science, Technology and Industry for National
Defense.
</P>
<P>
The commission will coordinate with relevant departments of the
Central Military Commission to take charge of producing and
supplying military equipment, and formulating and implementing
military scientific research programs.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the commission for national defense will be
responsible for working out development programs and regulations
for various military industrial trades and implementing sectoral
management.
</P>
<P>
And it will join the State Economic and Trade Commission in
working out programs for manufacture of goods for civil use by
military enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Coal Industry will be turned into the State
Coal Industry Bureau. The Ministry of Machine-Building Industry
will be reorganized into State Machine-Building Industry Bureau.
The Ministry of Metallurgical Industry will be turned into the
State Metallurgical Industry Bureau. The Ministry of Internal
Trade will be reorganized into State Internal Trade Bureau. The
national councils of Light Industry and of Textile Industry will
be made the State Light Industry Bureau and State Textile Industry
Bureau. All these bureaus will be subjected to administration by
the State Economic and Trade Commission.
</P>
<P>
The commission and its bureaus under its administration are
responsible for formulating and implementing sectoral programs and
regulations. The bureaus will not manage businesses directly, and
the sectoral programs and regulations will be issued in the name
of the commission.
</P>
<P>
Whereas the Ministry of Electric Industry will not be kept and
the State Electric Company has been formed, and the administrative
functions concerning electric industry will be incorporated into
the State Economic and Trade Commission.
</P>
<P>
The State Grain Reserve Bureau will be turned into a state
bureau under the State Development Planning Commission.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0119 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Swine Fever Kills 100 Pigs in W. Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Swine fever has killed at least
100 pigs in Hoima district of western Uganda since last October,
"The New Vision" reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Charles Byakora, a local councillor and poverty alleviation
official in the district, told a meeting Monday that local
piggery farmers informed him about the disease since October last
year.
</P>
<P>
The symptoms of the disease include loss of weight and lack of
appetite of the infected animals.
</P>
<P>
Frank Rwakabwohe, the head of planning, development and
rehabilitation program (PDRP) in the district, advised local
farmers to keep the environment clean.
</P>
<P>
"Good feeding and clean environment is the best treatment of
the pigs," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
