<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Detailed Plan on Restructuring of State Council (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With the merging of administrative functions of the Ministry of
Chemical Industry, China Petroleum and Natural Gas Corporation,
and China Petroleum and Chemical Industry Corporation, the State
Petroleum and Chemical Industry Bureau will be set up and
subjected to the administration of the State Economic and Trade
Commission.
</P>
<P>
All oil and gas fields, refineries, petroleum and chemical
plants to make petrochemicals, chemical fertilizers and chemical
fibers as well as oil firms and petroleum filling stations under
the above-mentioned ministry and two related corporations will be
reorganized into two exceedingly large-scale petroleum and
petrochemical conglomerates and a number of companies specialized
in the production of chemical fertilizers and other chemical
products.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Forestry will be made the State Forestry Bureau
under the direct jurisdiction of the State Council, taking charge
of afforestation, protecting forests and guarding against and
controlling forest fire, and working out sectoral programs and
regulations.
</P>
<P>
In addition to changes to be effected in departments concerning
economic affairs, the State Science and Technology Commission will
be renamed Ministry of Science and Technology, and the State
Education Commission renamed the Ministry of Education.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Labor and Social Security will be set up on the
basis of the existing Ministry of Labor. It will set up the
unified social security administrative institution, whose
insurance businesses are undertaken jointly by the Ministry of
Labor, Ministry of Personnel, Ministry of Civil Affairs and health
departments, as well as medical security undertaken by the
Ministry of Health.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Personnel will take charge of the management of
polytechnical personnel and civil servants, appointment and
removal of leaders of large enterprises under the supervision of
the State Council, and dispatching of supervisory commissioners to
large enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The State Physical Culture and Sports Commission will not be
kept, the functions of which will be entrusted to the
All-China Council of Physical Culture and Sports, an institution
to be listed directly under the State Council.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Land and Resources will be established on the
basis of the Ministry of Geology and Mineral Resources, State
Bureau of Land Administration, National Bureau of Oceanography and
the State Bureau of Surveying and Mapping.
</P>
<P>
The new ministry will be responsible for the management,
protection and utilization of land, mineral and ocean resources.
The National Bureau of Oceanography and the State Bureau of
Surveying and Mapping will be retained as a state bureaus under the
ministry's jurisdiction.
</P>
<P>
Conceding the power of managing television network, the
Ministry of Broadcast, Film and Television will be turned into the
State Broadcast, Film and Television General Administration, which
will be listed directly under the State Council.
</P>
<P>
Within the state administrative departments, The Ministry of
Foreign Affairs, Ministry of National Defense, Ministry of
Culture, Ministry of Health, State Family Planning Commission,
State Nationalities Affairs Commission, Ministry of Justice,
Ministry of Public Security, Ministry of State Security, Ministry
of Civil Affairs, Ministry of Supervision and the Auditing
Administration will be retained.
</P>
<P>
Through readjustment and reorganization, there will be 15
institutions directly under the State Council and six offices of
the State Council. The plans for the reform of these institutions
and offices will be carried out with the approval after
examinations by the new State Council.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
