<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Number of HK Drug Abusers Drops in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The number of reported drug
abusers in Hong Kong totaled 17,555 in 1997, down 10.8 percent
from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
More encouraging was that the number of young drug abusers also
dropped by 14.3 percent compared with 1996, Commissioner for
Narcotics Clarie Lo quoted figures from the Central Registry of
Drug Abuse (CRDA) as saying Friday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a quarterly meeting of the Action Committee Against
Narcotics (ACAN), Lo said: "A total of 3,135 drug abusers aged
below 21 were reported in 1997 as compared with 3,656 in 1996."
</P>
<P>
There was also a small decrease in the number of female drug
abusers in 1997 when 2,216 abusers were reported compared with
2,429 in 1996, she said.
</P>
<P>
The decline in drug abuser figures was consistent with the
downward movement of drug-related factors such as reported crimes,
persons receiving treatment and admissions to drug treatment
agencies, according to ACAN.
</P>
<P>
Notwithstanding this observation, a thorough study on factors
affecting the drug abuse trend in Hong Kong was recently
commissioned by ACAN with a view to identifying the underlying
factors that affect the size, complexity and characteristics of
the drug abuse population in Hong Kong. The study will be
completed by 2000.
</P>
<P>
More resources will be devoted to stepping up the beat drugs
campaign this year. The budget for ACAN's 1998-1999 preventive
education and publicity program amounts to about 5.1 million HK
dollars (654,000 U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
