<HEADLINE> South Africa, Ethiopia Agree to Intensify </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 6 (Xinhua) -- South Africa and Ethiopia
have agreed to intensify with vigor and renewed commitment to the
cooperation existing between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
In a joint communique issued here Friday at the end of the
official visit to Ethiopia by South African Foreign Minister
Alfred Nzo, the two sides expressed their satisfaction on the
positive achievements so far made and vowed to further accelerate
the contact between the economic operators as well as the peoples
of both countries.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers of the two countries have also signed a
declaration of intent with regard to cooperation in wildlife
management.
</P>
<P>
