<HEADLINE> Cholera Kills 560 Ugandans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Cholera has killed at least 560
Ugandans and infected more than 12,100 others since late November
last year, ''The New Vision'' reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The epidemic broke out late last November during the peak of
El-Nino. In early January, the cholera deaths were estimated at 400.
</P>
<P>
The second wave of the attack fell mainly on Kabarole District
in the west and Mbale District in the east. Health experts have
been sent to Mbarara, Kabarole Districts in the west and Mbale
District to assess the situation.
</P>
<P>
Over 6,260 cholera cases were recorded with 249 deaths in the
Central Region, 5430 cases with 250 deaths in the East Region,
400 with 67 deaths in the West Region, and four without deaths in
the North Region.
</P>
<P>
To curb the spread of the epidemic, efforts have been made
to improve sanitation in the country. Health workers in Kampala,
Soroti, Mbale and Tororo districts are trained in water quality
survey to enable them to take appropriate actions if needed.
</P>
</TEXT>
