<HEADLINE> Hainan Province Issues Environmental Protection Plans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Hainan Province in south China has
issued an environmental protection plan for the Ninth Five-Year
Plan period (1996-2000) and a plan for the period up to 2010.
</P>
<P>
As the first of its kind in the province, the two plans raised
the objectives, tasks and measures in pollution control and
greenery projects on Hainan Island.
</P>
<P>
According to the plans, by 2000 Hainan Province will process 92
percent of its industrial waste gas and 84 percent of industrial
waste water as well as 60 percent of sewage and garbage.
