<HEADLINE> Shanghai Designates Auctioneers of Confiscated Items </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai today designated four
auction companies to sell confiscated items.
</P>
<P>
With the strengthening of the Chinese judicial system, the
public security bureaus, courts and other state bodies have
confiscated more items and commodities, some of which are from
officials convicted of corruption.
</P>
<P>
The four companies, including the Shanghai International
Commodities Auction Co. Ltd., are considered the best in the
sector, with annual business volume surpassing 12 million yuan and
have been in business at least two years.
</P>
<P>
China has nearly 1,000 auction companies. Shanghai has 50 such
companies, whose total annual business volume last year was almost
1.7 billion yuan, 800 million yuan of which came from confiscated
goods. 
</P>
