<HEADLINE> 90 Percent of Beijing Residents Use Gas to Cook Meals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- More than 90 percent of the 2.5
million local households use gas to cook meals, according to
Beijing's Municipal Public Utilities Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released by the bureau show that 100,000 local
households eliminated coal for cooking in 1997, bringing the total
number of household using gas to 2.3 million.
</P>
<P>
The completion of a long-distance natural gas transmission line
connecting central China's Shaanxi Province with the Chinese
capital through northwest China's Gansu Province and Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region is a leading factor in the changeover.
</P>
<P>
