<HEADLINE> Macao Inflation Rate Reaches 2.5 percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Macao's inflation rate was recorded
at 2.5 percent in January, latest official statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
on Friday show that the composite consumer price index (CCPI)
reached 103.9, up 2.5 percent from the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
The average CCPI for the past 12 months dating back from
January grew 3.3 percent from that for the previous 12 months
period.
</P>
<P>
January's price index of family appliances grew 0.7 percent
from last December, the index of foodstuff and non-alcoholic
drinks also rose 0.7 percent. But the index of transportation and
telecommunications dropped 0.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Macao has seen an economic slowdown since 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
