<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Flower Show Unveiled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong opened its annual
flower show at the Victoria Park on Friday to display a wide range of
spectacular plants from around the world.
</P>
<P>
Elsie Leung, secretary for justice, officiated the opening
ceremony of the flower show this morning, the first after Hong
Kong's reunification with China.
</P>
<P>
This year "Blooms in a New Era" has been chosen as the theme of
the flower gala, jointly organized by the Provisional Urban
Council and the Provisional Regional Council.
</P>
<P>
Hydrangea, known for its beautiful florets, is selected as the
theme flower at the show, which came to its 12th session this
year. The organizers said that they hope hydrangea to bring joy
and vitality to Hong Kong people.
</P>
<P>
More than 70 flower associations are participating in the
ten-day show. With tiny green plants, horticulturists from
southern China's Zhongshan city created statues of dolphin, an
oceanic animal taken as Hong Kong's mascot. Professional gardeners
from Beijing designed a map of China with thousands of flowers, to
illustrate the reunification of Hong Kong with the motherland.
</P>
<P>
The organizers have received a total of 2,300 entries for this
year's flower competition, an event held annually in tandem with
the flower show.
</P>
<P>
A variety of activities will also be organized, including
photographic competition, band concerts, talks on horticulture,
and demonstration of floral arrangements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
