<HEADLINE> NPC, CPPCC Sessions Conducive to HK's Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The successful opening of the
sessions of both the National People's Congress (NPC) and the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) will be
surely conducive to Hong Kong's development.
</P>
<P>
An article carried by Wen Wei Po on Thursday said the two
sessions will give an impetus to China's modernization drive and
at the same time bring benefits to Hong Kong's development in
various fields.
</P>
<P>
The article noted that during the sessions, a new state
leadership upholding Deng Xiaoping's theory and the policies of
reform and opening up will be elected.
</P>
<P>
This will not only ensure the country's political stability,
but also boost Hong Kong people's confidence in their future, it
said.
</P>
<P>
The article noted that the deepening of reforms in the country
will also help attract more investment from Hong Kong
industrialists and businessmen.
</P>
<P>
The emphasis of reform has been put on reorganizing or
canceling departments directly in charge of economic management
and reinforcing departments handling macro-economic control and
those enforcing the law and supervising law enforcement, and the
reform will change administrative patterns of the planned economy
in a relatively thorough way and facilitate the development of a
socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
So, it will help bring into play Hong Kong businessmen's
initiatives of investment in the inland areas so as to promote
Hong Kong's economic development, it said.
</P>
<P>
The article said that the reform of the state-owned enterprises
will provide a very good chance for Hong Kong businessmen,
rendering timely help to Hong Kong's economy.
</P>
<P>
It expressed the belief that the two ongoing sessions in
Beijing and the new Chinese leadership to be elected will take a
series of measures to promote the governing of the state by rule
of law so as to ensure the whole society's orderly progress.
</P>
<P>
This will be conducive not only to guaranteeing social
stability and economic growth in the inland areas, but also to
implementing the Basic Law and maintaining Hong Kong's stability
and prosperity, the article said. 
</P>
