<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Holds Reception to Mark International Women's Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Two-thousand Chinese and foreign
women attended a reception in the Great Hall of the People in
Beijing today to mark the 88th anniversary of the "March 8"
International Women's Day.
</P>
<P>
The social status of Chinese women has improved during the past
year, said Chen Muhua, vice-chairwoman of the Standing Committee
of the National People's Congress and president of the All-China
Women's Federation.
</P>
<P>
Such steps as implementing the Law on Protection of the Rights
and Interests of Chinese Women and the Program for the Development
of Chinese Women have been taken as follow-up actions to the
world's Fourth Women's Conference, Chen said at the reception.
</P>
<P>
The number of women elected to the Ninth National People's
Congress (NPC) and the Ninth Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), both of which are currently
holding their first sessions in Beijing, have increased compared
with previous years, she said, adding that the number of women
deputies to the Ninth NPC is 650, or 22 percent of the total,
while the number for the Ninth CPPCC is 341, or 16 percent of the
total.
</P>
<P>
China will hold the Eighth National Congress of Women, the last
of its kind in this century, in September. The session will map
out the trans-century program for women's development, Chen said.
</P>
<P>
She said that Chinese women are willing to expand exchanges and
cooperation with women in other countries and are ready to make
unremitting efforts to achieve the goals of prosperity and
progress for all women in the world.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the Chinese central government, foreign female
diplomats, foreign experts who are working in China and women from
various circles attended the reception.
</P>
<P>
Vice-premier of the State Council Qian Qichen, Vice-chairman of
the NPC Standing Committee Lei Jieqiong and State Councillor Peng
Peiyun were also present at the reception. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
