<HEADLINE> Pakistani Foreign Minister to Visit Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Foreign Minister Gohar
Ayub Khan will pay a four-day official visit to Japan starting
from Sunday, according to the Associated Press of Pakistan (APP).
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Tokyo, Gohar will discuss wide-ranging
issues of regional and international importance with Japanese
leaders, the APP quoted sources from the Foreign Office as saying
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Gohar is likely to avail the opportunity to brief his Japanese
counterpart on Pakistan's initiatives for peace in South Asia,
particularly the process of talks with India on the Kashmir issue,
said the sources.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that Gohar's visit is of special significance
in view of the growing relations between the two countries and
their joint efforts to establish peace and stability in the
region.
</P>
<P>
It will be an important visit both in the context of economic
relations and the promotion of diplomatic ties between the two
countries, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
Besides meeting with Japanese leaders, Gohar will also meet
with heads of multi-national companies and prominent investors to
seek foreign investment in Pakistan, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan and Japan enjoy excellent relations in all fields and
have identity of views on various regional and international
issues, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
Japan has been supporting Pakistan's efforts for establishing
permanent peace in Afghanistan, the sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
