<HEADLINE> Figures on 1997 Budget Implementation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Following are main figures on the
implementation of central and local budgets for 1997 as told by
Finance Minister Liu Zhongli at today's session of the Ninth
National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
-- Total revenue in the central finance for 1997 came to
481.964 billion yuan, 101.4 percent of the budgeted figure and an
increase of 13 percent over the 1996 figure;
</P>
<P>
-- Total expenditures in the central finance for 1997 amounted
to 537.964 billion yuan, or 101 percent of the budgeted figure and
an increase of 10.4 percent over the 1996 figure;
</P>
<P>
-- The central coffers had a deficit of 56 billion yuan, one
billion yuan less than the budgeted amount;
</P>
<P>
-- Total tax receipts amounted to 422.02 billion yuan, 102.2
percent of the budgeted figure. Income tax from state-owned
enterprises amounted to 34.306 billion yuan, 6.172 billion yuan
less than the budgeted figure. The stamp tax on securities
transactions came to 20.216 billion yuan, 16.216 billion yuan more
than the budgeted figure;
</P>
<P>
-- Among main expenditures in the central finance for 1997,
expenses for capital construction came to 43.656 billion yuan.
Expenses for tapping the potential of existing enterprises and
upgrading technology came to 3.51 billion yuan. Experimentation
and subsidies for key scientific research projects came to 11.067
billion yuan. Expenditures for support of agriculture came to
5.566 billion yuan. Expenditures for cultural,
scientific and public health undertakings amounted to 18.494
billion yuan. Expenses for national defense totaled 80.651 billion
yuan. Policy-related subsidies totaled 22.317 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
-- Central revenues from generation of debt in 1997 totaled
247.683 billion yuan;
</P>
<P>
-- Total revenue in local finance for 1997 amounted to
728.03 billion yuan, or 101.8 percent of the budgeted amount,
an increase of 12.5 percent over the 1996 figure;
</P>
<P>
-- Total expenditures in local finance amounted to 727.509
billion yuan, or 101.7 percent of the budgeted figure, an increase
of 13.8 percent over the 1996 figure;
</P>
<P>
-- Total revenue for the whole country in 1997 amounted to
864.2 billion yuan, an increase of 16.7 percent over the 1996
figure;
</P>
<P>
-- The ratio of revenue to GDP was 11.5 percent, up 0.6
percentage points than that of the previous year;
</P>
<P>
-Expenditures for the whole country totaled 919.706 billion
yuan, an increase of 15.9 percent over the 1996 figure -- 0.8
percentage points lower than the increase in revenue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
