Belgian gendarmerie military police, several senior leaders of the
terrorist Armed Islamic Group (GIA) of Algeria were arrested
Thursday during a double operation in Brussels, announced Belgian
Interior Minister Johan Vande Lanotte. Some of the eight GIA chiefs
arrested are of Scandinavian nationalities, and one of them is a
French national of Algerian origin, Farid Melouk, who was condemned
last month by a court in Lyon for terrorist attacks in France in
1995.
</P>
