-- The situation continues to worsen in Kosovo, Yugoslavia, as
Serbian forces launched Thursday a mass attack with tanks and
helicopters on a dozen villages in the mountain near Srbica in the
Dernica region, stronghold of the Albanian guerrillas ``Army of
Liberation of Kosovo.'' The European Union warned Yugoslav President
Slobodan Milosevic that a political solution is urgent for this
province in southern Serbia with 90 percent of its population being
ethnic Albanians.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The offensive by Serbian security forces against several
Albanian villages in Kosovo on Thursday killed at least 20 people,
while ethnic Albanians put the number of people killed since last
Saturday at 51, including six Serb policemen. The International
Contact Group on Former Yugoslavia will meet Monday in London for
emergency discussions on Kosovo, and the United States has sent a
severe warning to Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic.
</P>
<P>
-- Three French teenagers killed Wednesday with a revolver a
grocer near Rouen, northern France. The murder has triggered a
strong feeling of anger in the local population. 
