<HEADLINE> Australian Share market Closes Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The Australian share market
closed the week in positive territory following strong buying
support for market heavyweight BHP Co. LTD, the largest company in
Australia.
</P>
<P>
After a lackluster start, the all ordinaries index finished
14.9 points higher at 2667.6 points, just off its high of 2669.0
points.
</P>
<P>
Resources giant BHP led the market higher and was followed by
other major stocks.
</P>
<P>
BHP shares finished the day 43 cents firmer at 15.43 Australian
dollars with 7.5 million shares changing hands after two days of
roller coaster prices following the resignation of Chief Executive
John Prescott on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"It was a bit of a strange day today," Henderson Charlton Jones
Broker Brett O'Donovan said. "BHP found a hell of a lot of buying
support as it continued throughout the day ... it led to market."
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index was 16.7 points stronger at 4572.2 at
the close of trade Friday, while the all resources index ended
14.7 points up on 1148.4 points.
</P>
<P>
Global miner Rio Tinto added 30 cents to 19.40 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The banking sector was mixed with National Australia Bank up 16
cents to 20.05 Australian dollars, Westpac Banking Corp. up seven
cents to 10.24 Australian dollars, Commonwealth Bank of Australia
down three cents to 17.57 Australian dollars and ANZ Banking Corp.
down two cents to 9.88 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The banking index was 27.2 points firmer at 5448.9 points.
</P>
<P>
The gold index slid 3.7 points to 1091.7 points following the
Sydney gold bullion price which dropped to 293.10 U.S. dollars per
ounce from 295.75 U.S. dollars per ounce Thursday.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 269.32 million shares worth 532.24
million U.S. dollars with falls outnumbering rises 559 to 532.
</P>
</TEXT>
