<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bonded Zone in Tianjin Uses More Overseas Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The Tianjin Port Bonded Zone
absorbed 700 million US dollars in 1997, up 75 percent on the
previous year, thus retaining its leading position among the
bonded zones in China.
</P>
<P>
Established in May 1995 and opened in April 1996, the
zone ranks first among the country's 15 operational bonded zones
by bringing in a committed investment of 3.76 billion US
dollars, including 2.54 billion US dollars in overseas funds.
</P>
<P>
The zone has so far approved the establishment of over 3,000
enterprises with investors coming from 78 countries and regions
such as the United States, Japan, Canada, Singapore, Australia,
the Republic of Korea, Hong Kong and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
It also attracted investors from 25 Chinese provinces and
municipalities, said local officials.
</P>
<P>
The bonded zone currently involves processing, storage and
transport, trade as well as many other services.
</P>
<P>
There are now more processing projects launched in the zone,
with over 20 of them being large and medium-sized.
</P>
<P>
To attract more investors, constant efforts were made to
improve the facilities and services in the zone. So far, a total
of 1.1 billion yuan has been injected into infrastructure in the
seven-sq-km bonded area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
