<HEADLINE> Figures in China's Draft Budget for 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Following are main figures in
China's draft central and local budgets for 1998 proposed by
Finance Minister Liu Zhongli to the Ninth National People's
Congress (NPC), in session here since yesterday.
</P>
<P>
-- Revenue in the central budget for 1998 totals 530.919
billion yuan, 48.955 billion yuan more than the actual figure for
1997, or an increase of 10.2 percent;
</P>
<P>
-- Expenditures in the central budget total 576.919 billion
yuan, 38.955 billion yuan more than the actual figure for 1997;
</P>
<P>
-- The central budget will have a deficit of 46 billion yuan,
10 billion yuan less than the actual figure for 1997;
</P>
<P>
-- Main receipts in the central budget for 1998 are as follows:
tax receipts total 463.986 billion yuan, up 9.9 percent over the
actual figure for 1997; total domestic sales and value-added taxes
come to 341.336 billion yuan; income taxes collected from
state-owned enterprises total 38.634 billion yuan; and customs
duties and sales and value-added taxes on imported goods total 80
billion yuan;
</P>
<P>
-- Main expenditures in the central budget for 1998 are as
follows: expenditures for capital construction total 40.692
billion yuan; those for key scientific research projects total
12.457 billion yuan; those for supporting agriculture total 6.235
billion yuan; those for culture, education, science and public
health total 20.717 billion yuan; national defense expenses total
90.99 billion yuan; and policy-related subsidies total 23.475
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
-- Some 280.86 billion yuan worth of treasury bonds will be
issued at home and abroad in 1998;
</P>
<P>
-- Both total revenue and expenditures in local budgets come to
798.935 billion yuan;
</P>
<P>
-- National revenue totals 968.368 billion yuan, up 12.1
percent over the 1997 actual figure; expenditures total 1.014368
trillion yuan, up 10.3 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
