<HEADLINE> Improving Overseas Investment in Northeast China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Overseas investment in the
economic and technology development zone of Changchun, the capital
of northeast China's Jilin Province, is expected to top 360
million US dollars this year.
</P>
<P>
The bulk of that will be used for improving key industries like
automobile parts, farm and sideline products, fine chemicals,
electronics, and new building materials.
</P>
<P>
One of the country's state-level development zones, the
Changchun zone will try to attract more overseas investment this
year in various ways like build-operate-transfer (BOT) and with a
series of promotional activities.
</P>
<P>
The zone got 32 more overseas-funded enterprises last year,
with 290 million US dollars in total investment, 162 million US
dollars of which came from overseas. 
