<HEADLINE> Shandong to Promote Development of Electronics Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, March 6 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province has
set a goal to make its electronics industry the largest sector in
the local economy by early next century.
</P>
<P>
The industry is expected to become one of the province's
leading sectors by 2000.
</P>
<P>
During the next five years, Shandong has planned to invest 11.3
billion yuan in the construction of 114 key electronics projects
and in the development and use of nearly 20 new and high-tech
projects.
</P>
<P>
By the turn of the century, the electronics industry is expected
to generate 70 billion yuan in output value a year and to have six
state-level technological development centers.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the industry earned 13.8 billion yuan in sales and
its growth rate was 20-percentage-point higher than the
national average. 
</P>
