<HEADLINE> Preparations Completed for Xiamen Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The preparation work for a fair on
exports to Taiwan have largely been completed, according to the
fair organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
The fair is the second of a planned annual event to be held
on April 8-12 each year in this coastal city of southeast China's
Fujian Province. Attending the event will be representatives from
companies that export on their own, overseas-funded enterprises
and firms funded by investors from Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Last year's inaugural fair drew the active participation of
both inland enterprises and the leading industrial and
commercial groups in Taiwan, and has since helped to expand
cross-Straits trade ties.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics showed that Xiamen's exports to Taiwan soared
87 percent in 1997, while exports from the rest of the country to
Taiwan grew more than 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
An expected 1,500 to 2,000 business people representing
companies from 40 large- and medium-size cities -- including
Shanghai, Beijing, Shenzhen, Dalian and Ningbo -- will participate
in this year's fair, which has 300 exhibition booths.
</P>
<P>
A series of seminars and workshops will be held during the fair
to strengthen economic and trade cooperation between the inland
areas and Taiwan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
