<HEADLINE> Shanghai Agents Granted Certification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The Bureau of Industry and
Commerce in the east China municipality of Shanghai has granted
the first round of qualification certificates to 365 agents.
</P>
<P>
The move indicates that China's largest commercial center had
strengthened management over agents' operations.
</P>
<P>
Establishment of the municipality's first agency in 1992 has
been followed by rapid development of the industry. Some 4,000
related firms currently employ over 20,000 people.
</P>
<P>
The local government has attempted to ensure healthy
development by calling on firms engaged in business of agencies to
employ a prescribed number of qualified agents and to clearly
define their scope of business.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai also plans to closely monitor related firms to prevent
illegal operations. 
