<HEADLINE> Central China Province Improving Economic Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan Province had
a GDP of 408 billion yuan last year, 10.5 percent more than for
1996, according to the newly released provincial statistics.
</P>
<P>
Henan's economic growth rate leads the country by 1.7
percentage points. But, in 1991, its economic growth was 2.3
percentage points below the national average.
</P>
<P>
By 1993, its economy began growing more than the national
average and it is still continuing, according to the release.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the province produced 38.95 billion kg of grain, a
record high, and there were good harvests of cotton, oil-bearing
crops, livestock, and vegetables.
</P>
<P>
The province's added value of industrial goods were worth 163
billion yuan, 1.3 times the 1992 figure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
