<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0210 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yamaichi Australia Licenses Revoked: ASC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The Australian Securities
Commission (ASC) Friday revealed it had revoked Yamaichi
Australia LTD's securities and futures dealers licenses at the
brokerage's own request.
</P>
<P>
Yamaichi Australia is a subsidiary of the financially troubled
Japanese securities broker Yamaichi Securities Company LTD, which
ceased trading on November 24 last year.
</P>
<P>
"The ASC understands that at the end of March, Yamaichi
Australia will close its Sydney office and that it has not
undertaken any new business since November 24, 1997," the ASC was
quoted by the Australian Associated Press as saying.
</P>
<P>
The ASC said its own inquiries had not revealed any criminal
conduct by officials of Yamaichi Australia, who have disclaimed
knowledge of the allegedly criminal aspects of the transactions in
Japan.
</P>
<P>
ASC Chairman Alan Cameron said the corporate watchdog was
closely monitoring the various investigations in Japan into the
affairs of financial institutions with Australian subsidiaries.
</P>
<P>
"The ASC is particularly concerned to ensure that Australian
subsidiaries conduct their affairs properly according to the law
and industry standards and that any impropriety within parent
companies not flow through to the Australian market," Cameron
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
