<HEADLINE> Northwest China Province Increasing Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu Province had 62
more overseas-funded enterprises in 1997, bringing in 107 million
US dollars of overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 1,356 overseas-backed companies, with 2.3
billion US dollars of investment, 965 million US dollars of
that from overseas.
</P>
<P>
The growth in the number of companies is a result of local
efforts to bring in loans from overseas governments to improve
infrastructure, investment conditions, and outmoded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the province sent representatives to Southeast Asia,
South America, Western Europe, and the Commonwealth of Independent
States for trade talks. It also held a trade fair in the provicial
capital, Lanzhou, and got 256 million US dollars of overseas
investment by making 570 projects available.
</P>
<P>
Construction work on a number of these like a wind power plant,
digital microwave communications for agricultural use, and
dehydrated vegetables is under way.
</P>
<P>
The Lanzhou Electrical Machinery Plant has begun to provide
production equipment and technology for a 25-million-US-dollar
project in Iran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
