<HEADLINE> 21,000 Foreigners Visit Beijing University in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- China's prestigious Beijing
University received 21,000 foreign visitors and hired 299 foreign
teachers last year, an official with the university's publicity
office said here today.
</P>
<P>
Both figures rank first among China's universities, the
official said.
</P>
<P>
Among the foreign visitors, 102 were presidents or
vice-presidents of overseas universities. The visitors also
included the premier of Singapore, the president of Romania,
various foreign ambassadors to China and presidents or
deputy-presidents of a dozen famous international companies.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the university has established
exchanges and cooperation ties with 143 well-known universities in
40 foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the official said, foreign professors working in
Beijing University had helped start 40 new courses, most of which
were pioneering scientific subjects.
</P>
<P>
During the year, Beijing University also organized or
cooperated in 17 international semimars.
</P>
<P>
An incomplete statistics show that, since 1990, the university
has received 45 foreign heads of state and government. 
</P>
