<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asia's Largest University Library Completed in Beijing University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The new part of the Beijing
University Library has been completed and is expected to be put
into use in the second half of this year, making the entire
library the largest of its kind in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The new part of the Beijing University Library, located on the
southern bank of the well-known Weiming Lake and standing
side-by-side with the old one, is more than 26,000 square meters
in construction area and characterized by a classical
architectural style.
</P>
<P>
When it is put into use later this year, the whole area of the
Beijing University Library will reach 50,000 square meters, enough
to house seven million books as well as 4,500 readers.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing University Library now keeps 4.5 million books, the
largest among Chinese universities.
</P>
<P>
Li Ka-Shing, a businessman from Hong Kong, donated 10 million
U.S. dollars to the construction of the new part of the library.
</P>
<P>
The university will celebrate its centennial in May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
