<HEADLINE> Kenya News Agency to Be Computerized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Plans are under way to
computerize the Kenya News Agency (KNA) offices in Nairobi to
enable it compete effectively with other media houses, a high
official was quoted as saying by the Kenya Times Friday
</P>
<P>
Minister for Information and Broadcasting Joseph Nyagah called
for the installation of fax machines in all KNA offices as a
temporary measure before introducing computers when he toured the
new KNA offices Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the agency faces the risk of becoming irrelevant
unless it is receptive to the new technological development in
mass communication.
</P>
<P>
The minister stressed that efforts should be made to project
KNA as a serious and dependable news agency and urged KNA
reporters to diversify their news coverage by highlighting the
activities of the farmers and other success stories of the
private sectors.
</P>
<P>
In order to survive in the future, the minister said that KNA
and the Kenya Broadcasting Corporation (KBC) should stop
transmitting stale news to its subscribers. 
