<HEADLINE> Congress Reviews Post-poll Scenario in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 6 (Xinhua) -- As the balance of India's
political forces tilted to the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP), the
Congress reviewed Thursday the post-poll political scenario
concerning government formation and its future leadership.
</P>
<P>
Leading newspapers reported Friday that the Congress working
Committee (CWC) adopted a resolution Thursday evening unanimously
expressing its willingness to play a constructive role in the
process of formation of a stable government at the center.
</P>
<P>
The CWC, the highest policy-making body of the party, said its
aim is to enable all secular forces to work together to strengthen
the pluralistic character of the country.
</P>
<P>
Senior party leaders attending the three-hour meeting were
unanimous that the electorate had not given any categorical
mandate to the BJP, now the largest political force in the
multi-party country.
</P>
<P>
The CWC expressed its deep sense of gratitude and appreciation
of the efforts make by Sonia Gandhi to help the Congress in the
just concluded Lok Sabha elections.
</P>
<P>
The CWC formally requested Sonia Gandhi to help the party reach
a consensus on the choice of its leader in the parliament "to
ensure total unity in the party".
</P>
<P>
Observers here see this request as a beginning of the subtle
process of Sonia's takeover of the Congress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
