<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Late Chinese Premier Commemorated in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Late Chinese Premier Zhou Enlai was
praised here in Macao as laying the foundation of "one country,
two systems" concept and a model to be learnt from, according to a
Thursday seminar.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Macao Daily News, the seminar to mark the
100th birthday anniversary of the late premier yesterday also said
that Zhou had done a great deal of fundamental and pioneering work
in resolving the issue of Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of a dozen local grassroot organizations
including those from workers' unions, women's federation,
journalists and education groups praised Zhou as a great
revolutionary, statesman, strategist and diplomat who had made
outstanding contributions to the founding and building of the
People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
"Zhou made a perfect model of a great patriot and statesman
with his firm political stand, farsighted political vision, broad
political mind and great political wisdom," said Lau Cheok Va,
deputy secretary-general of the Federation of Macao Trade Unions.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Zhou had took firm actions to maintain the
economic and political stability in Hong Kong and Macao because he
started from the actual reality, they said, adding that Zhou's
attitude laid the foundation of the concept of "one country, two
systems."
</P>
<P>
participants in the seminar stressed that the best way to
commemorate the late premier is to learn from his lofty spirit and
contribute to Macao's smooth transition and handover of power with
further promotion the basic law of Macao and more active
participation in transitional affairs.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Enlai (March 5, 1898 - January 8, 1976) served as China's
first premier from 1949 when the People's Republic was founded to
1976.  
</P>
</TEXT>
