<HEADLINE> International Stone Building Materials Show to Open in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- An international exhibition of
stone building materials and relevant technology and equipment is
scheduled to open April 1 in Shanghai, the fifth of its kind in
the country, the State Bureau for the Building Materials Industry
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Since 1981, the country's stone building materials industry
grew at an annual rate of more than 30 percent.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the country exported 700 million U.S. dollars of
stone building materials, and imported nearly 150 million
U.S. dollars of such materials.
</P>
<P>
The country now has more than 400 overseas-funded companies
involved in the sector. The increased use of overseas investment
and cooperation with overseas partners is still one of the major
ways of expediting the country's building materials industry.
</P>
<P>
Factories and companies in the sector from nearly 100 countries
and regions are expected to attend the showcase event. 
</P>
