<HEADLINE> Annan Thanks for Support of Pakistan on Iraq Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 6 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary General Kofi
Annan has conveyed his thanks to Pakistan for supporting his
efforts for a peaceful resolution of the Iraq crisis.
</P>
<P>
In a letter addressed to Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif,
Annan expressed his confidence that he can rely on the support of
Pakistan in his efforts to secure the implementation of relevant
resolutions on Iraq, said a report by the Associated Press of
Pakistan on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"I know that as we seek to move the issue towards a successful
conclusion, I can count on the continued support of Pakistan, a
good and loyal friend of the United Nations," the report quoted
Annan as saying in his letter.
</P>
<P>
During the height of the Iraq crisis over arms inspection,
Sharif wrote to Annan, urging him to strive for a diplomatic
solution in order to avert use of force, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Sharif also stressed the necessity of implementation
of all U.N. resolutions whether they are pertained to Iraq,
Kashmir or Palestine, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The report said that Annan has agreed with Sharif that full
implementation of the U.N. Security Council resolutions is
critical to the maintenance of global and regional peace and
security. 
</P>
</TEXT>
