<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Largest Communications Equipment Market In Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, March 6 (Xinhua) -- A 70,000-sq.m. communications
equipment market in Shenyang, capital of northeast China's Liaoning
Province, is open for business and is claimed to be the largest in
the country China.
</P>
<P>
The market was built at a cost of 220 million yuan by China
National Post and Telecommunications Industry Corp., China
National Post and Telecommunications Appliances Corp., and the
city of Shenyang.
</P>
<P>
The market has helped turn Shenyang into a communications
equipment distribution center for northern China and is expected
to do 10 billion yuan in sales a year by the turn of the
century. A number of overseas and domestic communications
companies will open there.
</P>
<P>
China has two similar markets in Hangzhou, the capital of
Zhejiang Province, and in Guangzhou, the capital of Guangdong
Province. The two-year-old Hangzhou market has a
10,000-sq.m. space and does 4.6 billion yuan in sales a year.
</P>
<P>
At present nearly 100 big-name international companies have
involved themselves in China's communications equipment market
since China opened the market more than a year ago, which is
estimated to have done nearly 200 billion yuan in business a
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
