<HEADLINE> China to Issue Stamp for Beijing University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- China will issue a stamp to mark
the centennial of the establishment of Beijing University on May
4. This will be the first time that the country has issued a
commemorative stamp for a university.
</P>
<P>
The stamp, with a face value of 50 cents, has the school's
former site and its emblem, the west gate, on the design. The
stamp's designer, Yu Lu, is a teacher at the university.
</P>
<P>
The launching ceremony, which will be held on the university's
campus on May 4, will be attended by officials with the State
Education Commission, Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications and
a number of well-known scholars.
</P>
<P>
Beijing University, one of the most prestigious schools in
China, was founded in 1898 and is the country's first national
university in modern history. 
</P>
