<HEADLINE> More Overseas Companies Set Up Offices In Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 6 (Xinhua) -- An increasing number of overseas
institutions and enterprises have shown interest in doing business
in the port city of Tianjin, which is an important economic center
in north China.
</P>
<P>
Last year the city had 82 more representative offices of
overseas businesses, bringing the total number to 1,042.
</P>
<P>
Since 1990, overseas investment in Tianjin has continued to
rise. Last year, the city came the second place in China, after
Shanghai, in using overseas capital.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin will invite more European and American businesses this
year and wants to become an East Asian production base for
multinationals. The city has more than 11,500 overseas-funded
enterprises, with nearly 20 billion US dollars worth of overseas
investment. 
