<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wellington, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
closed lower on Friday, but recovered some of the losses in
morning trading which was affected by a sharp fall on Wall Street
overnight.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 7 points lower at 2273 with a turnover
of 65 million dollars (37 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the main leaders, Air New Zealand gained 2 cents to 203
cents, Fletcher Energy picked up 1 cent to 625 cents, Fletcher
Paper rose 2 cents to 243 cents and Telecom lifted 4 cents to 827
cents.
</P>
<P>
Weakers leaders included Brierley Investment, losing 4 cents to
111 cents, Carter Holt Harvey, easing 2 cents to 258 cents, and
Fletcher Building, diving 10 cents to 385 cents. 
</P>
