<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central China Province Developing Township Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Development of small towns has
contributed a great deal to the local economy of central China's
Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
The Hunan provincial government has announced that it will
complete construction of 1,000 townships and 1,000 rural towns
within three-to-five years.
</P>
<P>
As one of China's largest agriculture provinces, Hunan has
rapidly developed its rural economy in recent years, which has put
township construction high on the working agenda of the provincial
government.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997, the province had completed construction of
more than 3,100 towns and counties, with a population of 7.87
million, raising the number of residents in these townships to 28
percent of the province's total population.
</P>
<P>
Township construction has become a kind of investment. Last
year, the province worked out construction plans for 132
townships, 78 counties and 237 villages. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
