<HEADLINE> Whitaker Enters Drug Rehabilitation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Pernell Whitaker has entered a
drug and alcohol rehabilitation facility after reportedly failing
a drug test last week.
</P>
<P>
Whitaker submitted to the latest test as part of an agreement
after reportedly failing one following his October 17 fight
against Russian Andrei Pestriaev at Ledyard, Connecticut. He
agreed to random screening and was issued this test as part of
pre-fight preparation for his showdown with World Boxing
Association welterweight champion Ike Quartey in Las Vegas on
April 25.
</P>
<P>
Whitaker, a six-time former champion, could face a two-year ban
on title fights by the WBA. The fight with Quartey has been
postponed indefinitely. 
</P>
</TEXT>
