<HEADLINE> Myanmar Cracks Down on Bogus Cement Sale </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities have been
cracking down on sale of bogus cement in shops in Yangon, the
country's capital, arresting three local people for producing,
distributing and sale of forged cement, The New Light of Myanmar
newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The three, involved in the production, distribution and sale of
bogus cement in the capital, were captured by members of the
Myanmar Defense Services Intelligence and the Bureau of Special
Operations in Shwepyitha township on February 17.
</P>
<P>
The authorities impounded the bogus cement bags from shops in
the capital, taking action against the three, the report said.
</P>
