<HEADLINE> Sino-Swiss Airline Agreement on Increased Flights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Air China and Swissair have
reached an agreement on increasing the number of flights between
the two countries, today's International Business Daily reports.
</P>
<P>
Starting March 29, Air China will increase the number of
flights to Switzerland from one per week to two, and Swissair will
go from three flights weekly to four.
</P>
<P>
Air China will also take part in promotions offered by
Swissair in Europe, the Middle East, Africa, and North America,
the report says.  
