<HEADLINE> Netanyahu Suggests Madrid as Meeting Venue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu said here Thursday that a second international
conference on the Middle East peace process may be held in Madrid
again.
</P>
<P>
At a joint press conference after meeting with his Spanish
counterpart, Jose Maria Aznar, Netanyahu said the peace process
could be developed and a final agreement could be reached only
after Isreali and Palestinians held direct negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The first Middle East peace conference was held in Madrid in
1991.
</P>
<P>
He said he was willing to come to Madrid again to hold talks
with Aznar and Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat. It would be a
good way to renew the peace process in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
At the press conference, Aznar reaffirmed his country's support
for the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu arrived here at noon for his one-day visit to Spain,
the beginning of a four-day European tour which also includes
Italy, Germany and Norway and is an opportunity to express his
ideas about the situation in the Middle East. 
</P>
</TEXT>
