<HEADLINE> Centenary of Zhou Enlai's Birth Marked in Croatia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Croatia and China have jointly
celebrated the centenary of the birth on March 5 of Zhou Enlai,
Chinese prime minister from 1949 until his death in 1976.
</P>
<P>
In a banquet hosted by the Chinese Embassy and Croatia-China
Friendship Association, Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister
Mate Granic hailed Zhou as a great man who contributed to China's
developments and greatly influenced world diplomacy.
</P>
<P>
Ivica Kostovic, Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Science
and Technology, said the most important achievement of Zhou was to
bring China back into the international community.
</P>
<P>
An official from the Croatia-China Friendship Association said
that because of Zhou, China had become a stablizing factor in
Asia, and the principles of peaceful co-existence Zhou proposed
had influenced relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Croatians from all walks of life attended the banquet and
Chinese Ambassador Li Guobang spoke on Zhou's life and role in
China's recent history. 
</P>
</TEXT>
