<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Communist Party leader Visits Laos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 6 (Xinhua) -- General Secretary of the Communist
Party of Vietnam Le Kha Phieu arrived in the Lao capital of
Vientiane Thursday on a five-day official visit aimed at boosting
ties between their countries.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with Lao President Khamtay Siphandone, the two
leaders agreed to tap their full potential in developing
cooperation on the basis of equality and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
They also vowed to create favorable conditions together for
both countries to integrate into regional and world communities.
</P>
<P>
Both believed the entry of Vietnam and Laos into the Association
of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) would contribute to
strengthening mutual trust and deepening cooperation in the region.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of Cambodia, the two leaders expressed their
wishes to maintain their traditionally friendly relationship with
that country and hoped peace and stability would soon be restored
in Cambodia. 
