<HEADLINE> Four Teams Qualify for Semi-finals in Basketball EuroLeague </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Four teams qualified for the
seim-finals with 2-0 marks while other three berthes will be
decided on the third matches in the EuroLeague Men's Basketball on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Partizan Belgrade of Yugoslavia stunned Olympiakos of Greece
72-60 at home to claim their second quarter appearances in
straight.
</P>
<P>
Partizan, who lost to the eventual champions Olympiakos in last
year's quarter-finals, upset the Greeks 78-74 in the first of
best-of-three matches on March 3 in Athens.
</P>
<P>
Kinder Bolonia of Italy lined up with country-fellows Benetton
Trviso for quarter showups, as Kinder edged Estudiantes Madrid of
Spain 67-62 in away match and Benitoon defeated Olimpija Ljubljana
of Slovenia 70-61 on the road.
</P>
<P>
Kinder trounced the Spaniards 86-62 while Benetton scratched a
slim victory of 81-79 on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The fourth came from AEK Athens of Greece, who had no trouble
to eliminate Croatia Split of Croatia 62-54 in the second matches
of the playoffs. They wrapped up 136-100 in two matches to
advance.
</P>
<P>
In other three quarter-finals, all home sides made advantage of
partisans' supports, with Maccabi Tel Aviv of Israel disposing of
Teamsystem Bologna of Italy 88-72, PAOK Salonika of Greece
crushing Alba Berlin of Germany 81-60 and Barcelona of Spain
snatchign a 75-63 victory.
</P>
<P>
In Madrid, Estudiantes took an early lead but could not hold on
as Kinder fought back at 34-31 halftime.
</P>
<P>
The Kinders pulled away in the second half to go 47-37 up, and
were able to dominate the match though the Spaniards side chased
close to within just two points in finals minutes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
