<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 21 Die, Dozens Injured in Ecuador Mudslide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, March 5 (Xinhua) -- At least 21 people died and dozens
were injured in a mudslide on Ecuador's central northern coast
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Before dawn, part of a mountainside slid onto the village of
Rio Cana, 150 miles (240 km) south of the capital Quito, say
reports.
</P>
<P>
Rescue workers had to walk for one hour to reach the scene
because roads had been cut for two weeks by the torrential rains
which led to the mudslide.
</P>
<P>
Rescue workers were reported to have dug out three bodies, and
at least 18 others were still buried deeply.
</P>
<P>
Heavy rains arising from the El Nino weather phenomenon have
hit most areas of the country this year causing many deaths and
great damage.
</P>
<P>
Figures show that so far floods have left 139 people dead, 28
missing and made 30,000 homeless nationwide since the El
Nino-caused abnormal weather began to hit the region last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
