<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Reports on Finance, Budget, Institutional Restructuring Made (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Three reports on the country's
finance, budget and government restructuring were delivered here
this morning at the second plenary meeting of the First Session of
the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
Chen Jinhua, minister in charge of the State Planning
Commission, delivered a report on the Implementation of the 1997
Plan for National Economic and Social Development and on a Draft
1998 Plan for National Economic and Social Development.
</P>
<P>
He said implementation of the 1997 plan was good with high
economic growth and a low inflation rate, but there remain some
problems with the economy and social affairs which should be
resolved with more efforts through in-depth reform.
</P>
<P>
In his report, Chen Jinhua listed major tasks in economic and
social development in 1998: to stabilize and strengthen the
position of agriculture as the foundation of the economy and
develop all sectors of the rural economy; to improve the quality
of industrial operation and foster new areas for economic growth;
to maintain appropriate growth in investment in fixed assets and
readjust and optimize the investment structure; to continue to
develop an open economy and do better in opening to the outside
world; to strengthen the management of revenue and expenditures
and guard against and reduce financial risks; to follow a strategy
of developing the country through science; to step up efforts to
implement re-employment programs and continue to improve people's
living standards.
</P>
<P>
Finance Minister Liu Zhongli delivered a report on the
implementation of the central and local budgets for 1997 and draft
central and local budgets for 1998.
</P>
<P>
"On the basis of relatively large increases of the past four
years in succession, revenue in 1997 increased by a big margin.
The ratio of revenue to GDP has continued to rise. The increase in
expenditures for 1997 was still lower than the increase in
revenue. The central deficit has been further reduced," Liu
Zhongli said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0266 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Reports on Finance, Budget, Institutional Reform Delivered (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thanks to efforts to deepen reform, strengthen management and
effectively implement an appropriately stringent financial policy
in the past few years, the country's financial situation is
improving, he said.
</P>
<P>
Guiding principles for preparing the central and local budgets
for 1998 are as follows: to further strengthen agriculture; to
support reform of state-owned enterprises and improve the social
security system; to do better in opening to the outside world; to
tighten and improve macroeconomic controls, continue to carry out
an appropriately stringent financial policy, strive to increase
revenue, tighten control over expenditures and reduce deficits;
and to promote a sustained, rapid and sound development of the
national economy and all-round social progress.
</P>
<P>
"To maintain and further improve the good macroeconomic
situation in 1998, we shall continue to follow an appropriately
stringent financial policy and reduce the central budget deficit
by ten billion yuan from the actual figure for 1997," Liu Zhongli
said.
</P>
<P>
State Councillor Luo Gan, also secretary-general of the State
Council, explained a draft Plan Concerning Institutional
Restructuring of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
He said the plan is to establish a highly efficient,
well-coordinated and standardized administrative system with Chinese
characteristics which meets the need of a socialist market
economy.
</P>
<P>
Principles for the reform are: to change governmental functions
and separate administration from business operation; to establish
a simplified, unified and efficient administrative structure; to
readjust the responsibilities and powers of government
departments; and to promote the exercise of administration
according to law, Luo Gan said.
</P>
<P>
The plenary meeting will also decide on the establishment of an
additional special committee under the NPC and a namelist of the
chairman, vice-chairmen and members of the NPC Financial and
Economic Committee.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was presided over by Buhe, an executive chairman of
the presidium of the First Session.  
</P>
</TEXT>
