<HEADLINE> Gansu Province Reports Record Gold Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu Province
produced a record 9.537 tons of gold in 1997, an increase of 42
percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The figure meets the target set for the year 2000. Gansu became
one of the major gold producers in the country, said Wei Xihao,
director of the Provincial Gold Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Rich in gold resources, Gansu has built four production bases
which accounted for more than 80 percent of gold production in
the province last year.
</P>
<P>
China produced a total of 166.3 tons of gold in 1997, up 37.9
percent on 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
