<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gist of China's budget for 1998 (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Finance Minister Liu
Zhongli reiterated that China will continue to carry out an
appropriately tight financial policy this year.
</P>
<P>
The country is to further strengthen agriculture, support
reform of state-owned enterprises and improve the social security
system this year, he said in his report on the implementation of
the central and local budgets for 1997 and on draft central and
local budgets for 1998.
</P>
<P>
He delivered the report at the ongoing session of the Ninth
National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
According to the draft budgets, revenue in the central budget
for 1998 totals 530.919 billion yuan, up 10.2 percent over last
year.
</P>
<P>
Expenditures in the central budget total 576.919 billion yuan,
up 7.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
This leaves a deficit of 46 billion yuan, he said.
</P>
<P>
Both total revenue and expenditure in local budgets come to
798.935 billion yuan this year.
</P>
<P>
For the nation as a whole, in 1998, total revenue is expected
to be up by 12.1 percent over last year; and total expenditures up
by 10.3 percent, 1.8 percentage points lower than revenue growth.
</P>
<P>
China must work hard to successfully implement re-employment
projects for laid-off workers and allocate funds to ensure a
minimum standard of living for them, Liu said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0277 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gist of China's budget for 1998 (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At the same time, financial departments at all levels should
increase expenditures to guarantee the implementation of
enterprise reform measures such as those designed to disperse
redundant employees to other jobs in cities where experiment to
establish a modern enterprise system is conducted, provide loans
with interest borne by the state finance to help enterprises
having difficulty meet their payrolls, reduce the spindles of the
textile industry and return income taxes for the purpose of
increasing circulating funds to cities where experiment to
optimize the capital structure is conducted.
</P>
<P>
The country's grain reserves have increased considerably owing
to the good harvests of the past few years in succession. This has
resulted in sharp rises in expenses for grain reserves and
subsidies for surplus grain reserves, so that existing risk funds
for grain production cannot meet actual needs.
</P>
<P>
To encourage production, protect peasants' interests and ensure
implementation of the state policy of purchasing as much grain as
possible at protective prices, the central budget for 1998 will
add 3.7 billion yuan to the risk funds for grain production and
local budgets will be required to arrange for an increase of 5.55
billion yuan in expenditure.
</P>
<P>
This year the government will not levy customs tariffs and
value-added taxes on imported equipment which cannot be produced
in China as well as technologies for projects using high
technology and domestic and foreign investment projects encouraged
by the state industrial policy, resulting in a total import tax
reduction of about 10 billion yuan, Liu said.
</P>
<P>
"We shall appropriately raise the tax refund rate for exported
textiles, which will result in an increased tax refund of 4.5
billion yuan," he added.
</P>
<P>
Central budget expenditures for servicing domestic and foreign
debts in 1998 will amount to 234.86 billion yuan, and the deficit
for 1998 will come to 46 billion yuan. This requires that treasury
bonds worth 280.86 billion yuan will be issued at home and abroad
in 1998, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
