<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0279 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: "One Country, Two Systems" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- In his government work report
delivered Thursday at the First Session of the Ninth National
People's Congress, Premier Li Peng talked about "one country, two
systems." Following is a brief explanation of the term.
</P>
<P>
The concept of "one country, two systems" was first put forth
by Deng Xiaoping, the chief architect of China's reform and
opening to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
Since the Third Plenum of the 11th Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC), the concept has gradually come to
maturity and become a fundamental state policy.
</P>
<P>
It was first proposed for the solution of the Taiwan question.
Deng Xiaoping explained, "After the reunification, Taiwan can
continue to practice its capitalism, while the mainland maintains
its socialist system. But there must be only one unified China.
This principle can also be applied to the Hong Kong question."
</P>
<P>
The government work report endorsed by the Second Session of the
Sixth National People's Congress (NPC) in May, 1984, formally used
the term "one China, two systems" to summarize the CPC's principle
for addressing the Taiwan and Hong Kong questions to realize the
reunification of China. Later, the expression was changed to "one
country, two systems." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0280 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: "Three Favorables" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The following is a brief
explanation for the term "three favorables" used in the Government
Work Report delivered Thursday by Premier Li Peng at the First
Session of the Ninth National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
In 1992 when China's reform and opening to the outside world
entered a critical moment, Deng Xiaoping, the chief architect of
China's reform and opening-up, visited southern China and put
forward a criterion to judge whether a new development is
socialist or capitalist in nature.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping pointed out that it should be judged according to
the criterion of whether or not it is favorable for promoting the
growth of productive forces in a socialist society, favorable for
increasing the overall strength of socialist China and favorable
for improving people's living standard, or "three favorables" in
short.
</P>
<P>
After the 14th National Congress of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) in 1992, the "three favorables" criterion has become a
common view shared by all Party members and people throughout the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0281 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: "Crack Down on Crimes and Launch Special Campaigns" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng, in his Government
Work Report delivered Thursday at the First Session of the Ninth
National People's Congress, talked about "to crack down on all
criminal activities and launch special campaign to fight crimes
and social evils." Following is a brief explanation for the term.
</P>
<P>
To crack down on all criminal activities and launch special
campaigns to fight crimes and social evils are fundamental methods
to improve all facets of public security across the country.
</P>
<P>
Crackdowns are focused on severe criminal activities such as
violent crimes, gun-related crimes and group crimes, drug-related
crimes, and economic crimes such as embezzling, bribery and
misusing public funds.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, law-enforcement departments often carry out
special nationwide or local raids against social evils such as
prostitution, gambling, and the production and
spread of obscene materials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0282 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: "To Grasp with Both Hands and with Equal Emphasis" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng, in his government
work report delivered Thursday at the First Session of the Ninth
National People's Congress, talked about "to grasp with both hands
and with equal emphasis." Following is a brief explanation of the
term.
</P>
<P>
"To grasp with both hands" means to do two things at the same
time: one is to promote material progress, and the other is to
promote ethical and cultural progress.
</P>
<P>
"To grasp with equal emphasis" means to attach equal emphasis
to doing the two things. That is to say, material progress should
not be pursued at the expense of ethical and cultural progress.
</P>
<P>
The thinking was first put forward by Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Generally speaking, material progress refers to the improvement
of people's material life, while ethical and cultural progress
means advancement in people's intellect and morality.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping once said: "Socialist ethical and cultural
progress not only refers to education, science and culture, but
also covers the Communist ideology, ideals, beliefs, morality,
discipline, revolutionary stand and principles, and comradeship
between people."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
