<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0288 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuba Reaffirms Demand for End to U.S. Embargo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The Cuban Foreign Affairs Ministry
Thursday reaffirmed a demand for an end to the 35-year-old United
States economic embargo against the Caribbean nation.
</P>
<P>
Ministry spokesman Alejandro Gonzalez said that the blockade was
a complete failure, senseless and lacking moral legitimacy.
</P>
<P>
He recalled that several Cuban-American organizations on Monday
stated their opposition to the embargo.
</P>
<P>
The call came as Cuban Brigade General Aroldo Ferrer Martinez
urged Cubans to continue their vigilance against constant threats
by the U.S to the revolution.
</P>
<P>
The general was speaking in the eastern province of Santiago de
Cuba at a ceremony marking the 40th anniversary of the third front
against the forces of former dictator Fulgencio Batista.
</P>
<P>
He said that defending Cuba's independence became more
difficult as the U.S. blockade intensified. 
</P>
</TEXT>
