<HEADLINE> Robotic Lathe for Carving Developed in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, March 6 (Xinhua) -- A robotic lathe recently developed
in Mudanjiang of northeast China's Heilongjiang Province, has the
capacity to fashion traditional decorative wood patterns for
doors, windows and furniture.
</P>
<P>
The newly developed robotic lathe has made it possible for mass
production of related products. The traditional production
efficiency remains somewhat low due to the complicated process
involved.
</P>
<P>
Researchers note that the computerized robotic lathe can
produce complicated patterns which include irregular curves and
three-dimensional carvings.  
</P>
</TEXT>
