<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shell to Open Service Stations in Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Shell Oil Company is planning to
invest 1.5 million U.S. dollars to establish 100 service stations
in Venezuela starting in April, a source from the oil company
announced here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Shell is the first transnational oil company authorized to set
up offices in the South American country under an agreement signed
in February with the Venezuelan state oil company Petroleos de
Venezuela, according to the source.
</P>
<P>
The source said 500,000 U.S. dollars of the investment will be
used to upgrade existing service stations that will be converted
to Shell stations, and one million dollars will be used to build
new stations.
</P>
<P>
Thirty service stations will be located in Caracas, the capital
of Venezuela. Seventy stations will be scattered throughout other
Venezuelan cities. The source said Shell plans to set up a total
of 500 services stations throughout Venezuela. 
</P>
</TEXT>
