<HEADLINE> CPPCC Members Satisfied with Government Work Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Many members of the Ninth National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) said that the Government Work Report delivered
by Premier Li Peng yesterday is "practical" and that they "are
very satisfied with the report."
</P>
<P>
More than 2,000 CPPCC National Committee members heard the
premier's report in the Great Hall of the People here and later
discussed the report in 48 groups.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC members shared the view that China has made
remarkable achievements in reform, opening-up and the
modernization drive over the past five years and that the overall
national strength has considerably increased.
</P>
<P>
Xiao Zhuoji, an economist with Beijing University, said the
proposed eight percent economic growth rate for this year is
"practical and feasible."
</P>
<P>
"Such feasibility is demonstrated by better conditions of
resources, transportation and raw materials, abundant grain
supplies and better financial conditions," he said.
</P>
<P>
Liu Hongru, vice-chairman of the China Finance Research
Society, said that, with the separation of "policy" banking and
commercial banking, the regulatory and supervisory roles of the
central bank have strengthened.
</P>
<P>
However, he noted that the fundamental cause for bad loans lies
in the fact that banks lack decision-making power. "Such a state
of affairs should change," he said.
</P>
<P>
Xian Dingchang, academician of the Chinese Academy of Sciences,
said the emphasis on high technology by China's leadership
indicates that the government has a good command of the economic
development trend in the world and is aiming at long-term
development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
