<HEADLINE> Malaysian PM to Visit Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir
Mohamad will pay an official visit to Myanmar in the near future
at the invitation of Chairman of the Myanmar State Peace and
Development Council and Prime Minister Than Shwe, according to an
official announcement here Friday.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first visit of a Malaysian leader to Myanmar
in recent years.
</P>
<P>
In April 1996, Than Shwe went to Kuala Lumpur on a state visit,
during which an agreement between the two governments on economic,
scientific and technical cooperation was signed.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, the bilateral trade between
Malaysia and Myanmar stood at 151 million U.S. dollars in the
first ten months of 1997, up from 88.5 million dollars in the same
period of the previous year, indicating a balance of trade in
Malaysia's favor.
</P>
<P>
The statistics also show that Malaysia brought in capital of
587 million dollars in 25 permitted projects at the end of 1997,
standing as the fourth largest foreign investor in Myanmar after
Britain, Singapore and Thailand.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian-invested projects include infrastructural
development of Myanmar's Thanlyin-Kyauktan Industrial Zone in
Yangon, oil and natural gas exploration and production in the
coastal areas, generation and distribution of electricity in
southern part of the country, hotels, manufacturing and wood-based
industry.
</P>
</TEXT>
