<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Visitors in Upper Hand after First Leg in Euro Soccer Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Four visitor teams were put in the
upper hand with two victories and two draws on Thursday in the
first leg of the European Cup Winners' Cup quarter-finals matches.
</P>
<P>
Vicenza of Italy almost booked a berth for the semi as the
Serie A underdogs routed Roda JC Kerkrade of Netherlands 4-1.
</P>
<P>
Vicenza, who are struggling at the bottom half in domestic
league, put up an earlier lead with three goals in the first half,
all coming from headers.
</P>
<P>
Striker Pasquale Luiso scored a double and defender Davide
Belotti added another, meaning the Roda defence was not in the
class of Vicenza's offence.
</P>
<P>
Marcelo Otero gave the Italian team a 4-0 lead after 66 minutes
before Bob Peeters answered a late consolation for Roda.
</P>
<P>
English Chelsea were also in the driving seat in the return leg
as the Premiership club walked away with an crucial 2-1 win over
Real Betis of Spain.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to Norwegian striker Tore Andre Flo's pair in the first
12 minutes, the English hopefuls left their Spaniards opponents a
real toil in the late match.
</P>
<P>
Alfonso Perez headed in from close range one minute after
halftime for Betis, but their constant efforts in the second half
did little to change the score mark.
</P>
<P>
Germany's VFB Stuttgart coule be contend with a 1-1 draw with
Slavia Prague of the Czech Republic, who did not hold onto a gold
opportunity for a home win.
</P>
<P>
Stuttagrt scored the lone goal in the 51st minute through
Gerhard Poschner who capitalized a blunder of keeper Jan Stejskal
to level the match.
</P>
<P>
Slavia was up in the 40th minute when Karel Vacha scored an
easy goal as Marc Ziegler parried Lubos Kozel's shot into Vacha's
way.
</P>
<P>
Robert Vagner missed a late penalty after he was tackled down
by Thomas Berthold in the 72nd minute and was awarded a gold
chance.
</P>
<P>
AEK Athens of Greece could not find the back of the net in a
home clash against Lokomotiv Moscow of Russia as the tie ended 0-0.
</P>
<P>
The Russians solid defence kept AEK out of the area and, for
most of the time, the Greeks' attacks ended as long range shots.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
