<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 22 Killed in Latest Conflict in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Two Serbian policemen and 20
armed ethnic Albanians were killed Thursday in the latest conflict
in the troubled Kosovo province of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The Tanjug news agency quoted the Interior Minister of Serbia
as saying that the conflict took place in the region of Srbica,
about 30 kilometers west of the province's capital, Pristina.
</P>
<P>
The police also confiscated many weapons, including grenades
and bombs.
</P>
<P>
Tensions in Kosovo escalated on March 1 after an armed conflict
which led to the deaths of four policemen and 16 Albanians.
</P>
<P>
Ethnic Albanians, who account for 90 percent of the population
in Kosovo, have been seeking independence from Yugoslavia since
1981. 
</P>
</TEXT>
