<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0304 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fujian Plans Extensive Agricultural Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 6 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province has
worked out plans to establish 30 experimental areas focusing on
modern agriculture, according to an official with the provincial
agricultural bureau.
</P>
<P>
The experimental zones will be transformed into hi-tech farming
areas featuring well-developed infrastructure, experimental bases
for modern farming and technological training schools for farmers.
</P>
<P>
The zones will adopt new decision-making mechanisms, a complete
water and power supply system and a social security network
oriented to agriculture under the new socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
According to the plans, the construction will begin in the
coming June, with the zones expected to account for 60 percent of
increased local agricultural production by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
In the zones, technology-intensive agricultural undertaking
will replace the current labor-intensive farming. In addition,
some 40 percent of farm products will be processed locally and 80
percent of related products will be subject to commercialization.
</P>
</TEXT>
