<HEADLINE> Unknown Dinosaur Fossils Found in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, March 5 (Xinhua) -- A group of Argentine
paleontologists and geologists have discovered the fossilized
remains of at least three unknown species of dinosaurs in Neuquen
Province, in east Argentina.
</P>
<P>
Paleontologist Jorge Calvo said Thursday that the group has
found about 35 pieces of fossils and they were well preserved, but
"completely scattered."
</P>
<P>
According to preliminary geological and paleontological
studies, the bones were deposited on a flood plain during the
outflow of a river in the region about 85 million years ago.
</P>
