<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Property Management Companies Thrive in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Recent statistics show that some
1,960 property management companies are currently operating in
Shanghai, China's largest metropolitan area.
</P>
<P>
The said companies are responsible for managing properties
covering 120 million sq.m., or about 50 percent of the city's
total available housing.
</P>
<P>
The city's booming real estate market has resulted in the
establishment of an average 10 property management companies per
week since 1996, a sharp contrast to the fact that the sector was
almost nonexistent only a decade ago.
</P>
<P>
The diversified sector includes state-owned, collective,
corporate, private and foreign-funded businesses. Some 7,400
staffers working for the companies hold academic and professional
titles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
