<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0318 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Harmattan Disrupts Flights in Nigeria Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Flight disruptions again took a
heavy toll Wednesday in almost all airports across Nigeria as
airlines could not operate their normal passenger service due to
poor visibility caused by the recurring harmattan haze.
</P>
<P>
Only the airports in the capital Abuja and Port Harcourt in
the south were confirmed Wednesday night by airlines officials as
having the capability to accommodate flights.
</P>
<P>
The haze of Harmattan, a seasonal hot, dry and dust-laden wind
originated from the Sahara, usually causes very poor visibility,
which also adds difficulties to motor drivers.
</P>
<P>
The poor visibility led to a suspension of domestic flights
all over Nigeria for several days running at the turning of this
year, forcing many passengers to resort to travel by motor.
</P>
<P>
Lack of advanced airport equipment is one of the major factors
that explain the vulnerability of the local airlines to weather
impact.
</P>
<P>
International flights were not affected even in the heat of
the harmattan haze this season, which extends from November to
March. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0319 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Refuses to Extradite German Scientist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Brazil rejected Germany's
request to extradite a German scientist charged with selling
nuclear technology to Iraq before the 1991 Gulf War.
</P>
<P>
Germany accused scientist Karl-Heinz Schaab, 63, of supplying
Baghdad authorities with information about uranium enrichment.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian Federal Supreme Court considered that
Schaab committed a political crime, but the Brazilian law bars the
extradition of people involved in breaches of this kind.
</P>
<P>
The German scientist was detained on December 11, 1997, in Rio
de Janeiro while trying to obtain information about the census of
foreigners in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
