- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- UN Secretary-General Kofi Annan on Thursday
appointed Prakash Shah of India as his Special Envoy in Iraq for
an initial period of six months.
</P>
<P>
The UN chief's move came amid the difficulties arising from
time to time in the relations between Iraq and the United Nations
and the need for improved lines of communication between the
Government of Iraq and his office in order to help avert the
development of difficulties into fully fledged crises threatening
to undermine international peace and security in the area.
(Annan-Special Envoy-Iraq)
</P>
