<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shaanxi Undertakes Ecologically-Sound Agricultural Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, March 6 (Xinhua) -- A project in northwest China's
Shaanxi Province is expected to create a bright future for
agriculture there, even during long periods of drought.
</P>
<P>
Although Shaanxi is regarded as an important agricultural area,
it is hindered by its dry weather. So, the provincial government
has made an effort with ecologically-sound agriculture projects to
stop soil erosion and plant trees and grass on 65 percent of the
province's land.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi is divided into three natural zones in its northern,
middle and southern parts and six ecological zones to improve
low-yield grain fields, curb soil erosion and develop water saving
irrigation, build agriculture products bases, and get the most out
of farmland.
</P>
<P>
Along with these six, the province will have six pilot projects
in ecologically-sound agriculture, dryland agriculture,
sustainable utilization, rich soil, and organic food. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
