<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves 336 Million U.S. Dollar Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved on
Thursday two loans totaling 336 million U.S. dollars equivalent
for two projects in Brazil.
</P>
<P>
First loan of 186 million dollars is earmarked for Rio de
Janeiro mass transit project. This project will help improve the
mass transit system of the city of Rio de Janeiro.
</P>
<P>
The project will benefit thousands of low-income households in
the city's metropolitan region, which has 9.8 million inhabitants
and is one of the largest in the world.
</P>
<P>
The project will develop a fully-integrated urban
transportation system and reduce the operating subsidies received
from the state, as the private sector is given a larger role in
operation and management.
</P>
<P>
Another loan of some 150 million dollars will be used for
Brazil's second water modernization project.
</P>
<P>
This project will help improve the country's water supply and
sewerage services in the poorest regions, expanding coverage for
the poor and improving the quality of service.
</P>
<P>
Improved environmental conditions will also contribute to the
recovery of beaches as well as to increased tourism and
recreational activities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
