<HEADLINE> Virtue Party Becomes Biggest in Turkish Parliament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The newly formed Virtue Party (FP)
became the biggest party in the Turkish parliament on Thursday
when six independent lawmakers jointed it.
</P>
<P>
The FP now has 140 seats in the 550-member legislature,
surpassing the Motherland Party, a longtime partner of the current
coalition government.
</P>
<P>
Most of the FP parliament members are ex-deputies of the former
Welfare Party (RP) which was banned in January for its strong
Islamic color.
</P>
<P>
A ruling by the Constitutional Court said that the RP had
become a center of the pro-Islamist political force and posed a
threat to Turkey's secularism.
</P>
<P>
Some analysts fear that the FP will follow the former RP and
become a new mouthpiece of the Islamists in the parliament.
</P>
<P>
FP leaders has repeatedly said the FP is a new party and
different from any other political parties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
