<DOCNO> XIE19980306.0346 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Albright Adds Madrid to Travel Plans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 5 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright will visit Madrid next week in addition to
Italy, Germany, France, Britain, Ukraine and Canada to discuss the
situation in Iraq, State Department announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, State Department spokesman James Rubin said
that Albright plans to fly to Madrid after meetings in London on
Monday. After Madrid, Albright will travel to Ottawa as previously
scheduled.
</P>
<P>
During talks with Spanish Foreign Minister Abel Matutes, "she
will convey our sincere appreciation for Spain's critical role and
continued public support during the latest crisis, and will also
discuss other issues of mutual concern," Rubin said.
</P>
<P>
Prospects of U.S. air strikes receded last week after U.N.
Secretary-General Kofi Annan struck a deal with Iraq to allow U.N.
arms inspectors to visit previously closed presidential sites with
diplomatic escorts to look for biological or chemical weapons.
</P>
<P>
Albright is scheduled to leave on Thursday for his six-day
tour. The first stop will be Kiev.  
</P>
</TEXT>
